job_information.description:
Location: Waterloo,Ontario,Canada

This is an opportunity in the exciting and fast-growing transportation technology industry.  Public transit is being transformed from a system of static, scheduled fixed-routes, to a dynamic on-demand network, and you’ll be one of the pioneers shaping this transformation. You’ll join a robust and rapidly growing client success team.

As a Business Data Analyst, you’ll be responsible for working directly with clients in face-to-face virtual or in-person meetings, analyzing client operations data, working with project managers on project implementations,  running service simulations, assessing key performance indicators, proactively driving client operational improvements, and providing technical systems support for multiple clients. You will develop a deep understanding of urban mobility challenges faced by transit operators.  You will become an expert on RideCo’s technology platform and data-driven design and operation of transportation services.

Your day-to-day responsibilities will include:

  • Program and client management: Plan and launch client projects as per the project timeline. Support communication and coordination between project stakeholders including transit planners, senior management, marketing, and operations staff. Work closely with the client through the entire project lifecycle and post-launch operations, prioritizing requests and fostering a strong relationship focused on desired customer outcomes and world-class customer experience.
  • Implement transportation services: Work together with project managers, solutions engineers, and client stakeholders to develop and implement transportation solutions that fit the needs of the customer. Translate client requirements into technical solutions leveraging the RideCo platform. Utilize a keen eye for detail to manipulate service parameters to meet the precise needs and goals of the client. 
  • Support new service launches: Setup, test, and tune system parameters, run simulations, oversee training, soft launch, monitor KPIs on launch week and make ongoing system changes as needed.
  • Data analysis and performance reporting: Perform ad-hoc data analysis tasks to compare service performance against goals, evaluate trends, and proactively identify areas for improvement. Collaborate with data engineers to design performance analysis reports spanning rider user-experience, driver user-experience, marketing, operating efficiency, and unit economics. Review the performance reports with stakeholders and the client operations team on weekly face-to-face client meetings to generate insights and actions. Collaborate with project managers to develop end to end executive  business review presentations for senior stakeholders.
  • Run simulations and optimize service design: Perform simulations to analyze performance and operational KPIs. Iterate on the service model by tuning and optimizing dozens of parameters such as dynamic routing engine settings, vehicle count and mix, supply positioning, service frequency, location and density of potential stops, and demand models. Collaborate with the client, operations managers, and other key stakeholders throughout this process. Support the client in setting targets and KPIs for the service prior to launch.
  • Provide technical support: Provide ongoing technical systems and analytics support to operations managers. Advise them on using the system’s dashboards and interpreting the data. Perform system configuration changes based on feedback from operations staff, drivers, and passengers.

Who We Are (Mode Mobile)

Mode Mobile builds products that allow millions of users to earn rewards from the content, communities, and experiences they already love. Our ecosystem spans mobile apps, web properties, media, and emerging social platforms, each generating rich datasets ready to be explored, optimized, and scaled.

We operate at startup speed, own outcomes directly, and value people who are both analytical and action-driven. As we expand our data capabilities across business units, we‚Äôre seeking a Senior Data Analyst who can dig deep, uncover insights, investigate anomalies, and elevate decision-making across product, growth, engineering, and operations.

Our Team and Culture Drive Our Success

Our team is the heart of our culture.  We value innovation, collaboration, and curiosity, with a passion for getting things done.  We strive to hire and cultivate the best team members and foster a culture of open communication and transparency.  We are driven and hard-working but also committed to having fun along the way.  We allow OKRs to guide us, assume positive intent, sometimes agree to disagree and commit, honor our commitments, seek to accomplish more with less, and encourage everyone to speak up as our team owns our company‚Äôs success.

The Role

The ideal candidate has exceptional SQL and Python skills, thrives in ambiguous environments, and brings rigor to data quality, analysis, and storytelling. Our Krakenites are a world-class team with crypto conviction, united by our desire to discover and unlock the potential of crypto and blockchain technology.

What makes us different?

Kraken is a mission-focused company rooted in crypto values. As a Krakenite, you‚Äôll join us on our mission to accelerate the global adoption of crypto, so that everyone can achieve financial freedom and inclusion. For over a decade, Kraken‚Äôs focus on our mission and crypto ethos has attracted many of the most talented crypto experts in the world.

Before you apply, please read the¬†Kraken Culture¬†page to learn more about our internal culture, values, and mission. We also expect candidates to familiarize themselves with the Kraken app. Learn how to create a Kraken account here.

As a fully remote company, we have Krakenites in 70+ countries who speak over 50 languages. Krakenites are industry pioneers who develop premium crypto products for experienced traders, institutions, and newcomers to the space. Kraken is committed to industry-leading security, crypto education, and world-class client support through our products like Kraken Pro, Desktop, Wallet, and Kraken Futures.

Become a Krakenite and build the future of crypto!

Proof of work

The team

At Kraken, data is both a strategic asset and the foundation of trust with our users, partners, and stakeholders and the data team is the backbone of decision-making.

We‚Äôre looking for a Data Analyst, Product to join our team remotely! The #1 goal of this role is to elevate decision-making by uncovering emerging trends and root causes, and by developing tools to drive insight and actions that give full visibility into product performance and business growth.

Beyond technical expertise, success in this role depends on being a true business partner who combines data-driven insights with strategic thinking to shape growth initiatives, guide decision-making, and drive measurable impact across the organization.

In this role, you‚Äôll own end-to-end data management from building and maintaining datasets and pipelines to designing dashboards and insights for the Product team. Additionally, you will work on experimentation infrastructure, launching an A/B testing system together with your team and contributing to other experimental projects to ensure the data team is constantly evolving and growing.

You will be, quite literally and quantitatively, defining success on a daily basis for our Product and leadership teams. Join us and be part of a team where data is not just an asset but our language, our tool, and our future.

The opportunity

  • Act as a trusted business advisor who influences decision-making for the growth team and deeply understands the business, both inside and out

  • Own the design of dashboards, metrics, and reports, turning data into actionable insights for the growth team, cross functional partners, and the leadership team

  • Dive into large, complex datasets/logs to turn your findings into scalable data models necessary to facilitate reporting, analytics and ML models

  • Lead cross-functional projects with analysts, scientists, engineers, and product teams to build data pipelines using Airflow, Python, and modern ETL frameworks

  • Develop and automate reporting of key performance indicators of various Kraken‚Äôs products at scale

  • Develop high-quality code for pipelines and dashboards, incorporating software engineering best practices

  • Deliver insights that shape growth direction through clear, data-driven storytelling.

Skills you should HODL

  • 3+ years of experience in data analysis and data management within the financial services industry, ideally gained in a fast-paced, high-growth environment

  • Hands-on experience using dbt (data build tool) to model and organize marketing, product, or performance data for reporting and decision-making

job_information.title: AI & Data Analyst
job_information.description:
DATA ANALYST - POWER BI SPECIALIST
THE INTELLIGENT SOLUTIONS GROUP
WINNIPEG, MANITOBA, CANADA

Convergence Networks is one of North America’s leading managed service and managed security providers. We are a service company focused on helping clients leverage technology as a strategic tool and proactively protecting their business. We are fueled by providing outstanding service and sharing our passion for innovative technology as part of our integrated solutions.  

POSITION SUMMARY

The Intelligent Solutions Group (ISG) at Convergence Networks is looking for a Power BI Specialist to transform data into clear, actionable insights for our clients. In this role, you’ll design data models, build intuitive dashboards, and help clients adopt modern, data‚Äëdriven practices.

 WHAT DOES OUR DATA ANALYST - POWER BI SPECIALIST DO? 

  • Conduct exploratory analysis and present insights to non‚Äëtechnical audiences
  • Partner with client stakeholders to define KPIs and deliver impactful reporting solutions
  • Build data models, data connections, data queries, DAX measures, and high‚Äëquality Power BI dashboards
  • Prepare datasets and semantic models for Copilot and Microsoft AI experiences
  • Deliver training, documentation, and self‚Äëservice BI best practices

WHAT ARE THE REQUIRED SKILLS?

  • Experience delivering end‚Äëto‚Äëend solutions via Power BI and Microsoft Fabric
  • Ability to coach clients through defining business needs, then designing and building related solutions
  • Strong SQL, ETL, query building, and data modeling skills
  • Clear communication, data storytelling, and stakeholder engagement
  • Proactive, detail‚Äëoriented, and adaptable to evolving requirement

WHAT ARE THE QUALIFICATIONS I NEED TO HAVE? 

  • Currently hold or ability to get certification - PL-300: Power BI Data Analyst Associate
  • Power Automate experience
  • Experience deploying AI/Copilot readiness, metadata, and semantic modeling
  • Azure AI Platform experience

WHAT IS THE WORK ENVIRONMENT LIKE? 

  • Normal office working conditions. Work requires regular sitting/standing at a desk, working with a computer. This position requires standing, walking, sitting, using   hands, seeing, reaching, talking, writing, and hearing; it may require occasionally carrying or lifting equipment if working on-site. 
  • Position requires contact with others - in meetings, by phone or by email. Interactions focus on data collection, problem solving, needs analysis and technical work. Interactions are initiated in person or electronically. Position may require some trave to customer sites

WHY SHOULD YOU WORK HERE?  

  • Work on meaningful analytics initiatives across industries that transform client business processes
  • Help organizations advance into an AI‚Äëenabled workplace and deploy cutting-edge technologies
  • Collaborate and learn with experts across various disciplines to give our clients the best experience possible
  • Grow through certifications, client engagement, and a supportive team culture
  • Group benefits plans, including medical, dental, vision in US and health savings and supplement insurance (including dental) in Canada, including retirement plans (401k and RRSP). 
  • We believe in personal and professional growth. We offer regular internal training opportunities, as well as training and certification reimbursement so we can help you grow. 
  • We believe feedback makes us better. You can expect regular meetings with your manager and quarterly conversations about your performance and growth. 
  • Many teambuilding and company events throughout the year so you can get to know your teammates on a more personal level, as well as have some fun (families are often included as well). 

PERFECT FIT… 

If this sounds like your type of place and you can wow us with your spectacular skill set, then we would love to hear from you!  

 

We are an equal opportunity employer and invite diversity in our applicants; our differences make us stronger! We welcome and encourage applications from qualified candidates of all races, sexes, colors, religions, sexual orientations, disabilities, ages, and gender identities. Accommodation is available upon request for candidates taking part in all stages of the selection process.

job_information.title: Senior / Lead - Data Analyst III - Pipeline Inline Inspection
job_information.job_title_raw: Senior / Lead - Data Analyst III - Pipeline Inline Inspection
job_information.description:
Description


Position Summary:


Data Analysis Level III is responsible for analyzing In-Line Inspection (ILI) data and verifying accurate sizing of identified pipeline anomalies. Capable of performing all data analysis activities at an expert level: data setup, Data Quality Assessments (DQA‚Äôs), data searches, feature identification and classification, automated and manual sizing validation, QAQC checks, process and procedure developmental support, and technology advancement support. Acts a Subject Matter Expert (SME) for the Data Analysis Department as well as other departments throughout the company. Provides training to data analysis personnel enabling successful progression through training programs, evaluations, and competence levels.  


Responsibilities:

  • Safety shall always be the top priority.
  • Work in a team environment, collaborating and sharing knowledge and experience.
  • Prioritize daily tasks to ensure on-time delivery of assigned reports and tasks.
  • Understands and leads compliance with API 1163, ASNT ILI-PQ, and POF, as needed. 
  • Evaluate and analyze data that has been acquired during an In-Line Inspection.
  • Perform Data Quality Assessments (DQA‚Äôs) in a timely and accurate manner.
  • Create and correlate Wall Thickness verification tables.
  • Feature categorization and evaluation, sizing, application of anomaly interaction rules and standard / non-standard analysis.
  • Correlate analysis results to inspection data from previous inspections.
  • In-field inspection data correlation and verification, as needed.
  • Prepare high quality Prelim, Final and other reports by performing quality checks and remaining acutely focused on meeting or exceeding customer expectations.
  • Aid Sales, Engineering, Project Management and Operations with the risk assessment of future ILI surveys to help ensure Entegra tools will successfully navigate and collect data from a Data Analyst point of view.
  • Assist Operations and Engineering to collect tool data results for RCA documentation
  • Assist in standardizing processes and procedures.
  • Assist in training data analysis personnel.
  • Operational Excellence: Actively participate in continuous improvement initiatives, consistently working towards the achievement of individual and team goals.
  • Additional Duties: Perform all other duties as assigned.

Requirements

  • College/University Degree or diploma preferred; or equivalent experience preferred
  • Minimum 3 years of experience in analyzing MFL, Geometry and IDOD pipeline inspection data.
  • Data Analyst Level III certification. 
  • Strong work ethic with a can-do attitude.
  • Advanced proficiency with operating relevant customized and over-the-counter computer software applications.
  • Demonstrated ability to deliver timely, accurate, and complete results.
  • Capable of making independent decisions/recommendations which can have immediate or time dependent consequences associated with pipeline integrity. 
  • Requires a strong ability to multi-task while avoiding distractions. 
  • Willingness to handle repetitive tasks
  • Requires pattern recognition and spatial thinking skill. 
  • Must be customer focused, have excellent attention to detail and a strong ability to work in a team environment.
  • Knowledge of PHMSA Part 192 and 195 regulations, API, NACE and ASME standards and recommended practices.
  • Demonstrates a commitment to integrating the ENTEGRA¬Æ Core Values into daily work and life. ‚Äî Be Innovative. Be Devoted. Be Honest. Be Accountable. Be Genuine. Be Industrious. Be Stewards. Be Excellent.

Employment Details:

  •  Work Location: Woodbridge, ON L4L 5Z9, Canada - Global Technology Center 
  • Department: DA - Data Analysis
  • Workplace Type: On-site
  • Job Type: Regular Full Time

Benefits:

  • Medical, Dental, and Vision Insurance
  • RRSP match
  • Paid Vacation & Holidays
  • Life & Disability Insurance
  • Professional Development Opportunities

Who We Are:

ENTEGRA¬Æ is the global leader in Ultra-High Resolution (UHR) pipeline in-line inspection technologies, driving innovation in the realm of pipeline integrity. We are a dynamic and forward-thinking company, driven by experienced and talented individuals, advanced processes, and cutting-edge technology. Our commitment is unwavering as we strive to revolutionize the landscape of in-line inspection, setting new standards for excellence.


Entegra is an Equal Opportunity Employer

ENTEGRA¬Æ is committed to a diverse and inclusive workplace. job_information.title: Data Analyst - Mid-Level
job_information.description:
Ready to accelerate your career?

Clara is the fastest-growing company in Latin America. We've built the leading solution for companies to make and manage all their payments. We already help over 20,000 large and growing businesses operate with agility and financial clarity through locally issued corporate cards, bill pay, financing, and a powerful B2B platform built for scale.

Clara is backed by some of the most successful investors in the world, including top regional VCs like monashees, Kaszek, and Canary, and leading global funds like Notable Capital, Coatue, DST Global Partners, ICONIQ Growth, General Catalyst, Citi Ventures, SV Angel, Citius, Endeavor Catalyst, and Goldman Sachs - in addition to dozens of angel investors and local family offices. 

We‚Äôre building the financial infrastructure that powers high-performing organizations across the region. We invite you to join us if you want to be part of a fast-paced environment that will accelerate your career and support you to do some of the best work of your life alongside a passionate and committed team distributed across the Americas.

 
 

We are looking for a Sr. Data Analyst who will:

  • Own the full analytics delivery lifecycle, from requirements to production BI.
  • Design and maintain data models, semantic layers, and curated datasets.
  • Translate business needs into clear metrics, KPIs, and analytical frameworks.
  • Develop reports and dashboards to support business decisions and self-service analytics.
  • Conduct data analysis to identify trends and patterns.
  • Collaborate with data engineers and scientists to ensure data quality.

 

Our requirements for this position are:

  • Degree in Data Science, Statistics, Mathematics, Economics or related areas.
  • Experience with SQL and database manipulation.
  • Experience in data analysis and extracting insights.
  • Concepts of statistics and exploratory modeling.
  • Familiarity with visualization tools
  • Fluent in English

 

Additional Skills & Plus:

  • Basic experience with Databricks.
  • Practical experience with ETL or ELT processes.
  • Data Integrity and Quality: strong emphasis on maintaining data integrity and quality.
  • Excellent teamwork and communication skills.
  • Creative problem-solving mindset.
  • Attention to detail.
  • Highly responsible, given the financial nature of our company.
  • Innovative and proactive, taking initiatives.
  • Strategic thinking and ability to set goals and achieve them.

Why join Clara

At Clara, you‚Äôll have the autonomy, speed, and support to make meaningful impact ‚Äî not just on your team, but on how organizations are run across Latin America.

Who we are

  • We‚Äôre the leading B2B fintech for spend management in Latin America.

  • Certified as one of the world's fastest-growing companies, a Great Place to Work, and a LinkedIn Top Startup.

  • Passionate about making Latin America more prosperous and competitive.

  • Constantly innovating to build financial infrastructure that enables each of our customers to thrive.

  • Product-led, high-talent-density culture ‚Äî designed for builders who raise the bar.

  • Proud of our open, inclusive, and values-driven environment.

Are you looking for more than a job? At World Vision Canada we offer challenging careers that change the lives of children all over the world and it will change yours too. Come and be part of a team of 400 Canadians with a vision for the world: Life in all its fullness for every child.

You will experience Christian faith in action helping to make real and lasting change in the lives of the world’s most vulnerable children. Join the World Vision Canada team and be part of a powerful and effective force for good:

For Children. For Change. For Life.



 

Position:

Data Analyst

Reports to:

People Manager

Position Term:

Full-Time Temporary (Until November 6, 2026)

Primary Location:

Mississauga, Ontario, Canada

Workplace Type:

Hybrid

 

 

Job Purpose

The Data Analyst serves as a general consultant to the business on analytics initiatives, empowering stakeholders with actionable insights that drive smarter decisions, stronger strategies, and measurable outcomes. 

 

Partnering with stakeholders and development teams, the Data Analyst defines requirements, applies appropriate analytical approaches, and delivers end-to-end solutions, including dashboards, reports, and workflows. 

 

This role also supports and enhances the organization’s BI and analytics infrastructure, promotes data literacy, and ensures sustainability through clear documentation and scalable solutions. 

 

Success requires advanced analytical expertise, strong data visualization skills, and the ability to communicate insights effectively across teams.

 

 

Responsibilities

 

  • Equip business partners to make informed decisions by acting as a technical and strategic partner, consulting on analytics needs and solutions
  • Collaborate with stakeholders to define requirements and determine appropriate and effective analytical approaches
  • Deliver high quality, decision ready insights that influence strategies and drive measurable business outcomes by extracting, analyzing, and validating data from various sources using statistical, diagnostic, and predictive techniques
  • Influence strategies and tactics by presenting analytics results in clear, concise formats that highlight recommendations and business value
  • Strengthen BI capabilities by supporting reliable tools, smooth migrations, and adoption of modern platforms
  • Increase organizational awareness and understanding of performance drivers by designing, developing, maintaining, and automating visually appealing, intuitive, and functional dashboards, reports, workflows, and models
  • Lead staff in adopting and utilizing analytics in day-to-day decision-making, ensuring insights drive opportunity identification and informed investments
  • Support in building organizational data literacy by clarifying definitions, communicating insights, and guiding stakeholders in effective tool usage
  • Strengthen long-term consistency by documenting data sources, methodologies, and workflows, and resolve data and reporting inefficiencies with scalable solutions

 

Qualifications

 

  • University degree in analytics, mathematics, statistics, computer science, business, or a related field; advanced degree an asset
  • Minimum of 5-7 years of progressive experience in analytics, business intelligence, or insights roles
  • Demonstrated expertise in statistical analysis, predictive modeling, forecasting, and advanced analytical techniques
  • Proficiency with BI, data manipulation, and data science tools such as Cognos BI, Power BI, SiSense, SQL, Python, SnowFlake, or comparable platforms
  • Proven ability to translate loosely defined business problems into clear analytical approaches and actionable solutions
  • Excellent communication, collaboration, and stakeholder management skills; able to convey complex insights in a clear and compelling way
  • Strong problem-solving skills with the ability to manage competing demands, establish clear priorities, and consistently deliver high-quality results within tight timelines
  • Curiosity, adaptability, and commitment to continuous learning and staying current with emerging analytics tools and methodologies
  • Experience working in Agile or iterative development environments, preferably

 

Why Consider Us?  

 

  • World Vision Canada has consistently been awarded Canada and GTA top employer awards.
  • We are Canada’s largest development, relief, and advocacy non-profit organization.
  • We embody an Agile mindset here.
  • We offer a family-friendly, caring, and flexible work environment.

 

#LI-Hybrid

 

 

 

We bring life-saving support in times of disaster. We help poor communities to take charge of their futures. We provide small loans and training that boost family livelihoods. We work with policy makers to change the way the world is run. Our Christian faith teaches us that every child, regardless of gender, faith or race, is a precious gift to the entire world - and that their wellbeing concerns us all. We shall never rest while children suffer in situations that can be changed.               

                                       

  

           


Canada's Top 100 Employers                          GTA Top 100 Employers

 

Our Core Values: We are committed to the Poor. We are Christian. We are Stewards. We value People. We are Partners. We are Responsive.


Qualified candidates must be able to demonstrate a commitment to the core values and mission of the World Vision partnership.
 

World Vision Canada takes our Safeguarding responsibilities seriously and we provide an environment that is safe for our child and adult beneficiaries. We have strong recruitment procedures to make sure the safest and most suitable people work with the children in our programs. We provide our staff and volunteers with ongoing supervision, support and training in their work with child and adult beneficiaries.
 

World Vision Canada welcomes and encourages applications from people with disabilities. Accommodations are available on request for candidates taking part in all aspects of the selection process.

job_information.description:
About us:

Spring Financial is revolutionizing financial access for Canadians, providing smart credit-building, mortgage, and lending solutions. Millions struggle with high-interest debt and limited financial options‚Äîwe‚Äôre here to change that.
As one of Canada‚Äôs fastest-growing fintech companies, annually we help 1 million customers explore their financing options with ease‚Äîonline, via text, or over the phone. Our dynamic, innovative team thrives on collaboration, growth, and making a real impact.
To learn more about our products please visit our website here: www.springfinancial.ca.


NOTE: This is a full-time, permanent, hybrid position in downtown Vancouver. 3 set days in the office and 2 WFH.


Job Overview:

As a Senior Data Analyst in Credit Risk at Spring, you operate at the intersection of analytics, data engineering, and business strategy. You bring together advanced analytical capability with technical depth to build the insights, pipelines, and frameworks that power our credit decisioning, forecasting, and portfolio monitoring. You take full ownership of the analytical lifecycle, from shaping ambiguous questions to delivering strategic recommendations that influence credit policy, product direction, and financial outcomes. You work across Snowflake, AWS, SQL, Python, BI tools, and AI tooling to uncover insights, modernize data flows, and support high-quality decision-making across the organization.


What you‚Äôll do:

  • Architect and guide the delivery of scalable, reliable data pipelines and analytical workflows supporting credit risk use cases across AWS and Snowflake.
  • Create advanced dashboards and reporting in Tableau, Hex, Power BI, or Qlik Sense for executive visibility and operational monitoring.
  • Analyze credit bureau data, market trends, and internal portfolio performance to surface insights that influence underwriting, pricing, and collections strategy.
  • Lead analytical projects from scoping through delivery, translating complex questions into structured frameworks and actionable recommendations.
  • Modernize legacy data flows, unify batch and streaming sources, and improve data models to support self-serve analytics and ML initiatives.
  • Collaborate with engineering, analytics, product, and finance teams to clarify ambiguous problems, assess risks, and propose scalable solutions.
  • Use Python and AI tools to perform advanced exploratory analysis, build predictive insights, and validate statistical outputs.
  • Partner with ML and Finance teams to ensure datasets meet the appropriate latency, accuracy, and governance standards.
  • Present findings and strategic recommendations to senior leadership, influencing direction and decisions across credit and product lines.
  • Mentor analysts and contribute to elevating Spring‚Äôs analytical rigor, documentation standards, and data-driven culture.

Requirements:

  • Proven experience in data analytics with exposure to credit risk, consumer lending, fintech, banking, or financial-services analytics.
  • Strong proficiency in SQL and Python for analytical workflows, modeling, and exploration.
  • Advanced skills in BI tools such as Tableau, Hex, Power BI, or Qlik Sense, with experience creating reports for senior management.
  • Experience working with cloud data platforms such as Snowflake and AWS.
  • Strong understanding of data modeling, schema evolution, and how pipeline design impacts downstream analytics.
  • Ability to independently lead cross-functional initiatives and align analytical work with business value.
  • Excellent communication skills and the ability to present insights clearly to senior stakeholders.
  • Comfort using AI tools to accelerate analysis, forecasting, segmentation, and hypothesis generation with appropriate validation.
  • Experience partnering with data engineering, BI engineering, and product teams on data requirements, pipeline improvements, and quality assurance.
  • Experience documenting dashboards, metric definitions, and analytical logic to support transparency and adoption.

What We Will Give You:¬†

  • Competitive annual salary ranging from $81,500-$107,500, reflective of experience and impact.
  • Comprehensive benefits package, including extended health, dental, and vision coverage ‚Äî with 100% of monthly premiums covered by the Spring.
  • GRSP matching program to support your long-term financial goals.
  • Transit-Friendly Employer (Transit allowance).
  • A modern, collaborative workspace in the heart of downtown Vancouver.
  • Ongoing career growth opportunities

---

Please note: Upon applying, our Talent Acquisition team will review your resume. If you qualify, we will reach out to learn more about your experience and answer any questions you may have about the role, benefits, compensation, and more. Due to high application volume, we may not be able to respond to everyone.



Thank you for your interest! We appreciate your time and look forward to reviewing your application!

This is not a generic ‚Äúbusiness analyst‚Äù role - this is a modern Data Analyst role requiring fluency in the data warehouse, strong analytical rigor, and the ability to work end-to-end (from raw or lightly modeled data through final insight, modeling adjustments, and BI deliverables). Your analytical standards, modeling practices, and approach to problem-solving will be developed and maintained in close partnership with the Data Team, while your project portfolio will be shaped by RevOps.

As an embedded analyst, you will serve as the analytical counterpart to RevOps leadership: helping to scope business questions, build robust data assets, design metrics and dashboards, and communicate insights that influence GTM strategy. A strong working knowledge of GTM motions in B2B SaaS will help you excel, though deep curiosity and strong fundamentals can also make up the difference.

Because this role sits at the intersection of RevOps and the Data Team, you‚Äôll have broad ownership and visibility across domains. You will work on everything from revenue funnel diagnostics and sales efficiency analyses to marketing cohort performance, capacity planning, retention/expansion patterns, and operational metrics that help our GTM leaders run the business. You will also contribute to the underlying data models and help mature the analytical operating system for GTM at Ashby.

If you‚Äôre a technically strong Data Analyst who enjoys owning the full analytical lifecycle, partnering directly with business stakeholders, and improving the modeling and data products that sustain an organization, this role will be an excellent fit.

Requirements

The essence of this role dictates that you must be analytical, conversant in statistical reasoning, and capable of managing the data you work with from inception through synthesis of results in the appropriate downstream assets. There are a lot of ways to meet those responsibilities. If the dot product of your skill vector with this requirements vector is close to 1, please consider applying, but please note it does not have to be 1.0.

  • Expertise in SQL-based data analysis

  • Strong in analytical and statistical thinking - you must be able to generate insights

  • Expertise with data visualization (i.e. visual communication of results)

  • Interest in working directly with business partners, i.e. go-to-market stakeholders, to identify and plan related analysis efforts

  • Proficiency building internal ‚Äúdata products‚Äù based on your analysis results, e.g. high-usage dashboards via BI tools (Looker, Tableau, etc) for various business partners

  • Excellent written and verbal communication. Ashby has a writing-centric culture, but you will also be responsible for direct collaboration with various teammates

  • Very detail-oriented: in your analysis work you can anticipate complications and identify bad-but-not-obviously-wrong data discrepancies

  • Proficiency in Python (primarily in the domain of data analysis and visualization)

You could be a great fit if

  • You identify as exceptionally curious by nature

  • You want to operate as a true Data Analyst embedded in a business function‚Äîcombining stakeholder-facing work with deep technical execution

  • You could pass as an ‚Äúanalytics engineer‚Äù or have working proficiency in dbt-based data modeling

  • You have been a first or early data analyst at a growing, fast-moving startup

  • You have strong working knowledge of GTM motions in B2B SaaS: sales, marketing, customer success, pipeline forecasting, and revenue analytics

  • You have an intuition for solving problems pragmatically and an eye for leverage

  • You enjoy collaboration and find reward in enabling other teammates to succeed

  • You have strong, experience-backed opinions about data products and data culture in a company setting

  • Familiarity with our data stack is a bonus, but not a requirement

  • Have a passion for refining the role of data within company environments, spanning everything from communication standards and data request management - you‚Äôll help shape this as Ashby grows

  • You can appreciate the whole distribution as much as a point estimator

Reasons not to apply

  • Spreadsheet-only analytical backgrounds are not a match for this role; fluency with SQL in a modern data warehouse is essential.

  • You do not enjoy working directly with non-analysts or other business stakeholders. This role will require working closely with teammates across the company as various data-related needs come up.

  • You are looking for consumer-scale data infrastructure projects. We have a huge and interesting set of data to work with (check out our data trends reports!), but we are a B2B SaaS company. Relative to B2C services, we might best be considered small but mighty :)

  • You are seeking an in-person work experience. Although there are hot spots of Ashby employees around the world, Ashby is a remote workplace. Rest assured, we do meet up in person for various events throughout the year!

  • You want to be on a large team of analysts. The Data Team at Ashby is extremely lean, so you will be primarily working with a data engineering partner, our first data analyst, and your manager (me!). That said, you will be working directly with many team members across the company, so your teammates in the analysis sense will be the diversity of folks you collaborate with from project to project.

Data Culture at Ashby

At Ashby, we draw a clear distinction between when to look to data for "the answer" and when to use data to aid principled thinking for decision making. In general, a primary consideration is whether or not data is needed to help clarify points of uncertainty. When data is considered necessary, a secondary consideration is to what depth data will be required. Data questions lend themselves to ongoing "what about..." or "what if..." explorations, which can be important in some situations but are not always necessary.

With these dynamics in mind, we do not foster an environment where every decision we make should be backed by data, but we do foster an environment where teammates ask whether or not data will fit the task at hand well. This, in turn, allows us to operate a lean team focused on projects where data provides true leverage to our overall business and product goals.

As a related but distinct point, Ashby‚Äôs data culture, as far as transparency and access goes, is very open. We share company-wide access to our financial standings, progress, goals, and generally make any data and reporting results broadly available. Outside of constraints related to whether a teammate has access to a particular tool, there are close to no constraints on access the state of the company as told by data or reporting. In general, we would like to continue and extend open access to data throughout the company (with your help!), but with consideration and not as a substitute for principled thinking :)

Ashby's Data Stack

As it will undoubtedly be a point of interest, a quick summary of our data stack is provided here. Our production database is postgres, which we integrate into a Snowflake data warehouse via Polytomic. All other business systems are integrated via Fivetran (the GTM stack involves HubSpot as our CRM and Stripe, most notably). We use Prefect for orchestration and dbt for data modeling. Frontend event tracking is done via Rudderstack. Data visualization and reporting varies, but the broader company is primarily served standardized analytics via Omni Analytics. For version control we use Git/Github (and Github Actions for CI/CD). As an Analyst, you'll be at liberty to work in a notebook or tool of your choice, but Hex is the burgeoning standard and likely recommendation. Internal documentation lives in Slab and dbt docs.

A core part of the data stack at Ashby is the actual people! As mentioned, we are a lean team, and the current structure is myself as the manager, a single data engineer and two data analysts. You would be our third data analyst joining the team, and the first data analyst embedded in the Go To Market organization. All members of the Data Team maintain a strong sense of ownership and agency in their work, but the broader responsibility comes with broader leeway.

Interview Process

Our interview process is thorough. We aim to ensure each person that joins the team is the right fit for Ashby and will provide ample information for you to assess if Ashby is the right fit for you. The process for this role is as follows:

  • Hiring Manager Screen (30 mins)

  • Take Home Assignment: Mini Analysis and Write-up (~3-4 hours)

  • Final Round - Virtual Onsite (~2.5, can be split into multiple days)

    • (45 mins) Analysis Projects Deep Dive

    • (30 mins) Working with Data Engineering

    • (30 mins) Working with Go-to-Market Stakeholders

    • (30 mins) Chat with a Founder

    • (15 mins) Follow-Up Conversation + Debrief with the Hiring Manager

Note: please do not reach out to the broader Ashby team requesting more information or time to connect. We will diligently review all applications in detail after the public posting period is over.

Benefits

  • Competitive salary and equity.

  • 10-year exercise window for stock options. You shouldn‚Äôt feel pressure to purchase stock options if you leave Ashby ‚Äîdo it when you feel financially comfortable.

  • Unlimited PTO, and we will encourage you to take it.

  • A minimum of 12 weeks of fully paid parental leave, covered by Ashby. For folks outside the US, it may be longer to be in line with regional requirements.

  • Generous equipment, software, and office furniture budget. Get what you need to be happy and productive!

  • $100/month education budget with more expensive items (like conferences) covered with manager approval.

  • If you‚Äôre in the US, we offer top-tier health insurance for you and your dependents, with 100% of premiums covered by Ashby. In other countries, we provide high-quality supplemental health insurance for you and your dependents, also fully covered by us.

Ashby‚Äôs success hinges on hiring great people and creating an environment where we can be happy, feel challenged, and do our best work. We‚Äôre being deliberate about building that environment from the ground up. I hope that excites you enough to apply.


If you've made it this far and are excited about Ashby, please apply and follow us on LinkedIn to stay up to date!

Ashby provides equal employment opportunities (EEO) to all employees and applicants for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, national origin, age, disability, genetics, sexual orientation, gender identity, or gender expression. We are committed to a diverse and inclusive workforce and welcome people from all backgrounds, experiences, perspectives, and abilities.

job_information.title: Data Analyst (product focused)
job_information.description:
THE COMPANY

We’re rapidly growing and looking for driven and customer-obsessed professionals to help our team revolutionize the career-services industry.

Career.io is dedicated to creating a better landscape for job seekers everywhere. Through our community of career experts and data insights, our brands —we empower professionals to take control of their careers, tell the best version of their career stories, and reach their full potential. 

We’re committed to helping job seekers write the next chapter of their careers and we want to help write yours, too! We hire for growth and longevity because we value the happiness and well-being of our employees.

THE ROLE

We’re seeking a product-focused analyst who will help the business find growth opportunities, explain performance, and support decision-making across Product and Marketing. The role is hands-on and broad: you will work on product and marketing analytics, KPI reporting, and measurement for new features and experiments. Work is prioritized by business impact and shipped iteratively.

You will also own the implementation behind your work: managing connection of sources, keeping ELT jobs healthy, building dbt models and marts, and maintaining consistent KPI definitions across dashboards and tools.

This is a 100% remote/work-from-home role.

 

THE KEY RESPONSIBILITIES

  • Identify growth opportunities and business problems, quantify impact, and help prioritize what to build next.
  • Own analytics projects end-to-end: requirements → implementation → rollout → stakeholder adoption.
  • Build and expand KPI reporting: define missing metrics, create dashboards, and measure new feature impact
  • Build and maintain the analytics stack: connect data sources, manage ELT/pipelines, and develop dbt models/marts.
  • Investigate metric drops/spikes, find root causes, and turn findings into actionable recommendations.
  • Product & marketing analytics: analyze funnels, activation/retention, feature performance, plus acquisition channels, attribution, and campaign performance.
  • Ensure data reliability by implementing tests, monitoring, and documentation.
  • Support experimentation: partner with the Product team to design experiments, monitor results, and evaluate impact. (edited) 

THE MUST-HAVES

  • 3+ years in Product/Data Analytics, Analytics Engineering, or a similar role (ideally B2C/SaaS).
  • Strong SQL and hands-on dbt (models, tests, docs).
  • Python for analysis and automation.
  • End-to-end data delivery skills: connect sources when needed, build production-ready pipelines, and design layered dbt models (staging, intermediate, marts).
  • Product analytics fundamentals: funnels, cohorts, retention/activation, segmentation, A/B testing basics.
  • Ownership mindset: you can take ambiguous requests, define success metrics, deliver a solution, and drive decisions.
  • Engineering mindset: Git, code reviews, clean code, testing, and documentation.
  • Strong stakeholder communication: align stakeholders, explain complex topics simply, and write clear documentation.
  • Experience with BI tools (Looker/Tableau/Power BI/Metabase or similar).

At Career.io, we believe that diversity in thought and cultural background leads to better teams and stronger companies. We seek talented, qualified employees, regardless of race, color, sex/gender (including pregnancy, gender identity, and gender expression), national origin, religion, sexual orientation, disability, age, marital status, citizen status, veteran status, or any other protected classification under country or local law. Career.io is proud to be an Equal Employment Opportunity Employer.

job_information.description:
Want to be part of a team that makes a difference? Come be part of the change. 

Since 1920, APEGA has been regulating the practices of engineering and geoscience to serve the public interest in Alberta. 

We are looking for energetic people who thrive in a dynamic, fast-paced, and challenging environment. You are committed to serving the community with integrity, accountability, and innovation, and capable of delivering exceptional service. If you reflect these values, have the knowledge, skills, and abilities to make a difference through your work, and are passionate about acting in the best interest of public safety – then come be a part of our diverse and inclusive team!

Position Summary

With the premise of protecting the public being the highest order priority, along with a community of members exceeding 75,000, APEGA acknowledges and embraces the criticality of data – its quality, security, privacy, accuracy, timeliness and integrity – as critical and imperative to core business, compliance obligations, and in support of APEGA’s overall trust and relevance. The Data Analyst role designs, plans, monitors, and enhances the organization’s data governance and data management functions.

The Data Analyst’s role is to assist in building, deploying, and maintaining data support tools, metadata inventories, and definitions for database file/table creation. This individual will also assist with designing data modeling/analysis services used to mine enterprise systems and applications for knowledge and information that enhance business processes.

Responsibilities

  • Work with Developers to coordinate the creation and management of data queries.
  • Design, develop, and maintain ETL processes to extract, transform, and load data from various sources into other storage systems.
  • Ensure data quality, optimize ETL processes, and collaborate with other team members to meet data integration needs.
  • Provide and apply quality assurance best practices for data analysis services across the organization.
  • Collaborate with unit managers, end users, development staff, and other stakeholders to integrate data management applications with existing systems.
  • Develop, implement, and maintain change control and testing processes for modifications to data models.
  • Create data definitions for new database file/table development or changes to existing ones.
  • Determine required network components to ensure data access, as well as data consistency and integrity.
  • Develop routines for end users to facilitate best-practice use of data management tools.
  • Work with Developers and Systems Analysts to monitor data management system details within the database, including stored procedures and execution time, and implement efficiency improvements.
  • Document processes and systems, assess data models, entity relationship diagrams and their respective technology integration points.
  • Consultative activities related to assessing and evaluating options and providing key recommendations.

Competencies, Skills & Attributes

Competencies

Knowledge, Skills & Abilities

Core:

  • Exemplifying Integrity
  • Fostering Communication
  • Results Orientation
  • Service Excellence
  • Teamwork

 

Core Leadership:

  • Decision Making
  • Ensuring Accountability
  • Inspiring Others

 

Functional:

  • Nurturing Innovation
  • Thinking Strategically
  • Knowledge and experience establishing functional, performance, stress and load, integration, regression, system as well as user acceptance testing
  • Knowledge of software development life cycle (SDLC), software testing life cycle (STLC), structured systems development concepts
  • Knowledge and experience preparing and using test strategies, plans, scenarios, cases and test data
  • Knowledge of test automation tools
  • Knowledge testing integrations between multiple commercial products and custom services such as Aptify, Sitefinity, Formatta, SQL and other services
  • Knowledge of testing ERP applications is an asset
  • Knowledge with data integrity testing
  • Experience using development and testing tools from Atlassian, Microsoft or other industry standard tools (e.g., Jira, Confluence, Azure DevOps, Zephyr)
  • Proficient in Microsoft Office tools
  • Experience using functional test automation tools (e.g., Katalon, Selenium, Cypress, TestComplete, etc.)
  • Experience managing software testing for enterprise level applications
  • Experience using SQL
  • Experience testing APIs
  • Strong analytical and research skills to identify and resolve issues
  • Able to evaluate user requirements and interpret system specifications
  • A team player with excellent interpersonal and communication skills
  • Able to provide user support and training during UAT
  • Attention to detail

 

Qualifications

  • University degree in the fields of Computer Science and/or Commerce/Business Administration

  • Strong understanding of how different functions (e.g., Regulatory, Finance, etc.) will have different data uses and requirements

The role functions to demonstrate an appropriate level of alignment between the strategic goals of the business and technology decisions. The Technical Solutions Analyst will be a subject matter expert pertaining to organizational technology and must have an understanding of core business functions, legislation, as well as industry standard technologies and toolsets. A primary focus is to identify and establish clarity between business drivers and needs to propose value producing, sustainable technology solutions.

Responsibilities

job_information.title: Senior Data Analyst
job_information.description:
General Bank of Canada is a Schedule 1 Chartered bank headquartered in Edmonton, Alberta, and part of the Wheaton Group. Our journey began in the 1950s with an entrepreneurial spark that has grown into one of Canada‚Äôs fastest-growing small banks, delivering innovative financing solutions across automotive, aviation, and commercial sectors.


At GBC, our core values of Trust, Discipline, People-Centric Approaches, and Innovation drive every decision we make. We leverage our nimble structure to pioneer forward-thinking banking solutions in the digital era. Proudly certified as a Great Place to Work for six consecutive years, we are dedicated not only to transforming banking but also to making a real impact in the communities we serve. Since 1969, our ongoing partnership with United Way has fueled volunteer initiatives, fundraising, and community programs that truly change lives. When you join our team, you‚Äôre contributing to a future where innovation and community go hand in hand. We love it here and know you will too!


The Opportunity

General Bank of Canada is looking for a permanent, fulltime Senior Data Analyst to join as a key contributor with the Bank‚Äôs Data, Technology and Innovation (DTI) team. Consistent with the growth trajectory of the Bank, this is an excellent opportunity for the right individual to contribute to building the Bank of the future with considerable potential for learning, growth, and advancement.


The Senior Data Analyst is responsible for analyzing and transforming data into meaningful insights that drive informed and strategic decision-making. This role will develop and maintain advanced analytical models, including statistical and machine learning models, as well as build dashboards, data extraction and transformation logic, as well as reports ¬†and dashboards to ensure accuracy and relevance in business processes.


The Senior Data Analyst will take a hands-on approach to advanced model development, data extraction, validation, and visualization, leveraging SQL, Power BI, Excel, and Python to support analytical needs across the organization. Advanced model development includes all components of the data science lifecycle, including exploratory data analysis (EDA), feature engineering, model evaluation and selection using appropriate statistical and machine learning techniques, as well as visualization of model and data output. Additionally, the role will contribute to data quality and governance efforts, collaborating with data engineers, architects, and business colleagues to ensure consistency and accuracy in reporting and analytics, while strengthening modeling rigor and supporting the growth of the organization‚Äôs data and analytics capabilities.


Position Responsibilities

  • Data Analysis & Modeling: Analyze complex datasets to identify trends, patterns, and insights that support data-driven decision-making. This includes the development of advanced analytical models for exception reporting, regulatory analysis, corporate performance evaluation, and forecasting to assess business impacts and opportunities. Apply statistical and machine learning techniques where appropriate to enhance accuracy and predictive capability.
  • Dashboard & Reporting Development: Design, build, and maintain interactive Power BI dashboards and reports, ensuring accuracy, performance, and usability. Automate reporting processes where possible and work with business teams to refine visualizations that support business objectives and enable self-service analytics.
  • Data Extraction & Transformation: Utilize SQL, Excel, and Python to extract, clean, and transform data from multiple sources, ensuring data quality and consistency. Build reusable queries, datasets, and feature sets to support self-service reporting, advanced analysis, and model development.
  • Advanced Analytics & Model Development: Conduct exploratory data analysis (EDA), feature engineering, and the development, comparison, and evaluation of statistical and machine learning models. Ensure models are validated, monitored, and refined to maintain accuracy and business relevance.
  • Data Governance & Performance Monitoring: Support data governance by ensuring accuracy, reconciliation, and compliance with quality standards. Monitor key business metrics, flag anomalies, and assist in identifying root causes and recommending corrective actions. Contribute to model governance practices, including documentation and performance monitoring.
  • Collaboration: Work closely with cross-functional teams to understand analytical needs, translate them into data and model‚Äëdriven solutions, and present findings in a clear and actionable manner. Provide guidance on analytical methods and the interpretation of model outputs.
  • Data Storytelling & Business Enablement: Communicate complex analytical and model‚Äëdriven insights in a clear, compelling, and accessible way. Help business units understand key drivers, model outputs, and their implications, and support education on data concepts, analytical approaches, and self-service tools to strengthen data literacy across the organization.
  • Continuous Improvement & Innovation: Stay current with industry trends and emerging technologies in analytics, data science, data visualization, and modeling. job_information.description:
Who we are

Samsara (NYSE: IOT) is the pioneer of the Connected Operations‚Ñ¢ Cloud, which is a platform that enables organizations that depend on physical operations to harness Internet of Things (IoT) data to develop actionable insights and improve their operations. At Samsara, we are helping improve the safety, efficiency and sustainability of the physical operations that power our global economy. Representing more than 40% of global GDP, these industries are the infrastructure of our planet, including agriculture, construction, field services, transportation, and manufacturing ‚Äî and we are excited to help digitally transform their operations at scale.

Working at Samsara means you‚Äôll help define the future of physical operations and be on a team that‚Äôs shaping an exciting array of product solutions, including Video-Based Safety, Vehicle Telematics, Apps and Driver Workflows, and Equipment Monitoring. As part of a recently public company, you‚Äôll have the autonomy and support to make an impact as we build for the long term.

About the role:

The Senior Data Analyst will be a core technical contributor to our Data Analytics team with deep expertise in driving data-driven decision-making through querying, structuring, and visualizing data. The Senior Data Analyst will work closely with cross-functional leaders, engineers, and product managers to translate business, product and technical questions into concrete quantitative analysis, and iterate on the output with stakeholders.

This is a remote position open to candidates residing in the United States and Canada. Relocation assistance will not be provided for this role.

You should apply if:

  • You want to impact the industries that run our world: Your efforts will result in real-world impact ‚Äì helping to keep the lights on, get food into grocery stores, reduce emissions, and most importantly, ensure workers return home safely.
  • You are the architect of your own career: If you put in the work, this role won‚Äôt be your last at Samsara. We set up our employees for success and have built a culture that encourages rapid career development, countless opportunities to experiment and master your craft in a hyper growth environment.
  • You‚Äôre energized by our opportunity: The vision we have to digitize large sectors of the global economy requires your full focus and best efforts to bring forth creative, ambitious ideas for our customers.
  • You want to be with the best: At Samsara, we win together, celebrate together and support each other. You will be surrounded by a high-calibre team that will encourage you to do your best.

In this role, you will: 

  • Translate data into strategic insights via memos, presentations, dashboards, etc. to support decision-making for operational and leadership teams 
  • Building analytical models to identify patterns, anomalies, and root causes (e.g., analyzing sensor temperatures to spot unhealthy devices)
  • Build relationships with technical and non-technical stakeholders to understand data structures and business priorities
  • Build a strong sense of product and data acumen (e.g. customer experience, data logging)
  • Perform a variety of exploratory analyses that help us understand the health of our products and identify opportunities for improvement and optimization
  • Champion, role model, and embed Samsara‚Äôs cultural principles (Focus on Customer Success, Build for the Long Term, Adopt a Growth Mindset, Be Inclusive, Win as a Team) as we scale globally and across new offices

Minimum requirements for the role:

  • 5+ years experience in a data-related role relevant (data science, data analyst, business analytics, business intelligence)
  • BA / MS or equivalent coursework in quantitative discipline (e.g., Statistics, Mathematics, Computer Science, Economics, etc.)
  • Proficiency in data manipulation and processing in SQL, Python, and/or R
  • Ability to communicate trends and learnings via data visualizations including Tableau
  • Ability to effectively share project statuses and take ownership of tasks while handling competing priorities
  • Ability to distill informal or ambiguous customer and business requirements into crisp problem definitions
  • Proven ability to communicate verbally and in writing to technical peers and leadership teams with various levels of technical knowledge
  • Curious about our data, our product and excited to have an impact

An ideal candidate also has:

  • A strong track record of cross-functional partnership 
  • Experience working with large datasets using distributed computing (e.g., Spark, Hive)

job_information.description:
YOU¬†never¬†MET A PROBLEM¬†

YOU COULDN'T SOLVE

The Opportunity

** This is a temporary full-time position for 12 months **
Internal Job Title: Analyst, Business Analysis

The word ‚Äúproblem‚Äù isn‚Äôt even in your vocabulary. You prefer to think of it as a challenge waiting for you to work your analytical magic. In fact, when one of your clients describes a challenging situation to you, your brain is already turning it into a¬†query. You love the idea of transforming data into critical information and knowledge and have a burning desire to seek out innovative new technologies that can be used to make sound business decisions.¬†¬†¬†

We‚Äôre looking for¬†a Business Data Analyst with a knack for data and the ability to shape a project from start to finish. Someone who can work with subject matter experts as well as business and operational leaders in order to determine requirements, define key performance indicators and develop insights into and solutions for business problems.¬†
¬†

A Place to Belong
AMA is more than a workplace; it‚Äôs a family. Together, we help protect the things that matter most to our more than one-million members‚Äîeverything from roadside safety to retail savings, food security to childhood well-being. And with operations that span automotive, registries, travel, insurance and more, the opportunities to grow with us are almost limitless!

Building on a century of proud service in Alberta communities, we‚Äôre passionate about making a meaningful difference in the places where we live and work. And that all begins with our people. As part of the AMA team, you‚Äôll enjoy: ¬†

  • Competitive wage
  • Employee-exclusive discounts on travel, insurance, memberships, and more
  • Ongoing professional development
  • Vacation earnings paid out with each pay period
  • Flexible work models that make sense for your lifestyle
    ¬†

Who You Are

  • Finding simple solutions to complicated problems and explaining them to others comes as naturally to you as breathing.¬†¬†
  • You don‚Äôt see a data table‚Ä¶you see a story waiting to be told; and you know just the query to tell it.¬†¬†

*This role is open to remote based candidates based in Canada with a preference for candidates based in Vancouver, BC* ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬†¬†
We‚Äôre looking for a Payments & Data Analyst to join our team and be part of our next stage of growth. As our Payments & Data Analyst, you will serve as a centralized resource for payments operations, customer data, and revenue reporting across the organization. This role is responsible for pulling, analyzing, reconciling, and reporting data across Salesforce, payment platforms, and finance systems, ensuring teams and leadership have accurate, consistent insights to support decision-making.


Partnering with stakeholders across Payments, Finance, Product, and the Senior Leadership Team, this role helps establish clarity, consistency, and confidence in company metrics, while also supporting the operational execution and performance of our payments function.

¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬†¬†

Who we are
At Traction Rec, community is at the heart of everything we do. We empower nonprofit organizations like YMCAs, Jewish Community Centers (JCCs), Boys & Girls Clubs of America (BGCA), and Salvation Army Kroc Centers to strengthen their communities through great technology built on the Salesforce platform. By enabling these organizations to deliver their services more efficiently, we help them focus on creating meaningful connections and driving positive change where it matters most.


We believe that business is a powerful force for good. As part of this belief, we‚Äôve committed to the Pledge 1% for the Planet, dedicating 1% of our time, product, profit, or equity to supporting environmental and community causes. This commitment reflects our dedication to creating a positive impact that extends beyond technology.


Our passion for community and innovation has earned us recognition, including:


  • Salesforce Nonprofit Sales Partner of the Year and ISV Partner of the Year
  • Globe & Mail's Top Growing Companies of 2024 and 2025
  • Deloitte's Technology Fast 50 winner 2024
  • Deloitte's Technology Fast 500 winner 2024 and 2025


At Traction Rec, we live our values: Community, Authenticity, Impact, Fun, and Growth. As a Living Wage Certified employer in British Columbia, we are dedicated to supporting not just the communities we serve but also the people who make it all happen‚Äîour team.


If you‚Äôre passionate about making a difference and want to join a company that puts community first, we‚Äôd love to have you on this journey with us. Together, let‚Äôs create stronger, healthier, and more connected communities.

¬† ¬†¬†

Skills
Traction Rec‚Äôrs come from a variety of backgrounds, and we are eager to find people that are from diverse backgrounds. For this role, you might have:


  • Experience working in a payments, SaaS operations, analytics, or business analysis role
  • Hands on experience working with payment data, transaction reporting, or payment platforms
  • Strong experience working with Salesforce, including reporting and data extraction
  • Advanced Excel skills, including pivot tables, formulas, and data analysis
  • Strong analytical and problem-solving skills with high attention to detail
  • Solid business and financial acumen with the ability to connect data to revenue, margin and operational outcomes
  • Ability to manage multiple requests and priorities in a fast-paced environment
  • Clear, professional communication skills and comfort working with stakeholders at all levels
  • Experience supporting finance, sales operations, customer teams, or payments function is a plus


What You Will Be Doing

  • Serve as the primary point of contact for payments, data, and reporting requests across all teams and the Senior Leadership Team
  • Own Salesforce reporting and data extraction across KPI, notably around customer usage, revenue, and payments performance.
  • Pull, analyze, and reconcile data from multiple sources, including Salesforce, payment processors, and finance systems.¬†
  • Build, maintain, and improve recurring and ad hoc reports using Salesforce and other analytics tools
  • Track and analyze key business metrics such as ARR, churn, expansion average, customer lifecycle, product adoption, transaction success rates, fees, chargebacks, and payout timing.¬†
  • Support the payments function with operational reporting, analytics, and insights to help monitor performance and identify optimization opportunities.
  • Monitor payment workflows and reconciliation processes to ensure accuracy, compliance, and operational efficiency
  • Support Finance, Sales Operations, and Customer teams with data for planning forecasting and performance tracking.¬†
  • Provide accurate, timely metrics and insights for executive and Board level reporting.¬†
    Design, build, and maintain dashboards and data visualizations to communicate payments, revenue, and customer insights to internal stakeholders
  • Identify opportunities to improve data quality, reporting processes, and operational visibility across payments and customer data.¬†
  • Translate complex payments and operational data into clear, actionable insights through dashboards, visualizations, and executive ready summaries for stakeholders across the organization
  • Participate in customer and external partner discussions, as needed. ¬† ¬†

¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬†¬†

Compensation
At Traction Rec, we are committed to a fair, market-based and equitable compensation structure. Our market data is refreshed on an annual basis to reflect the most current market conditions.


The starting salary band for this role is $90,000-$100,000. Starting salaries will vary within this range based on experience, skill level, and internal equity related to the role. ¬†

¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬†¬†

Please note that the range details above reflect the base pay only and do not include our competitive bonus program and benefits that we offer.


Our Approach to AI
At Traction Rec, we‚Äôre big fans of AI and we embrace it as a tool that helps us work smarter and more creatively. It may even have helped with this job description. job_information.description:
Join nesto ‚Äî proudly named Canadian Rocketship 2025*. A Deloitte Fast 50 company evolving alongside Canada‚Äôs top tech innovators and disrupting a 2.1 Trillion-dollar mortgage industry at light speed by building the mortgage ecosystem of the future.


BUILD lending technology with the best developers, AI engineers, and mortgage experts in the country. Work on a modern tech stack and a development framework designed to unlock your full potential and accelerate your career.


Why join us

  • Hypergrowth: Deloitte Fast 50 ‚Äî 3 years in a row
  • Tech community credibility: TechTO Canadian Rocketship 2025*
  • Industry leadership: CLA Lending Company of the Year ‚Äî 4 consecutive years
  • Talent magnet: CMP Top Mortgage Employer 2025
  • Trusted technology: powering major financial institutions across Canada
  • An entrepreneurial culture built on trust, speed, uncomfortable ambition, being stronger together, and a relentless obsession with our clients.


About nesto and Nesto Cloud

nesto is Canada‚Äôs leading provider of mortgage technology and financing solutions, managing $73B+ CAD in residential and commercial mortgages, with 1,000+ team members across 12 offices nationwide. You will be working on Nesto Cloud, Canada‚Äôs most advanced cloud platform, delivering end-to-end technology solutions for lenders in the digital age.

As Data Analyst your primary focus is the administration, development, and optimization of our reporting ecosystem. You will serve as the bridge between legacy and modern reporting, taking full ownership of our SSRS request queue while simultaneously building high-impact dashboards in Power BI. This role is ideal for a hands-on developer who is comfortable managing a busy ticket queue and driving the adoption of modern analytics.


Who You Are

  • A "Doer": You are comfortable jumping into a fast-paced environment and taking immediate ownership of the reporting backlog.
  • A Visual Storyteller: You don't just put charts on a page; you build dashboards that tell a clear story and drive action.
  • The "Admin" Mindset: You enjoy the organization and governance required to keep a BI environment running smoothly.


Key Responsibilities

SSRS Development & Maintenance (Core Responsibility)

  • Ownership of Requests: Handle all incoming requests for SQL Server Reporting Services (SSRS). This includes scoping and building new reports from scratch based on business needs.
  • Change Management: Execute change requests for existing SSRS reports, optimizing queries and adjusting layouts to match evolving business processes.
  • Troubleshooting: Diagnose and resolve issues with report rendering, data accuracy, or subscription delivery in a timely manner.

Power BI Development & Administration

  • Modern Visualization: Design, develop, and deploy advanced Power BI dashboards that are intuitive, performant, and visually compelling.
  • Environment Admin: Oversee Power BI Service administration, including workspace management, security roles (RLS), and gateway configurations.
  • Data Modeling: Translate business requirements into clean, functional data models (DAX/Power Query) that serve as a "single source of truth."

Stakeholder Collaboration & Governance

  • Requirement Gathering: Work directly with business units to understand their KPIs and translate them into technical reporting specifications.
  • Data Integrity: Partner with the Data Engineering team to validate underlying data in SQL Server and Azure SQL.
  • Best Practices: Champion reporting standards, ensuring all new builds follow internal UI/UX and data governance guidelines.

Required Skills & Qualifications

Technical Expertise

  • Experience: 3‚Äì5 years of experience in data analysis and BI reporting, preferably in Financial Services or FinTech.
  • SSRS Proficiency: Strong ability to design, develop, and deploy paginated reports using SSRS (Visual Studio / Report Builder). You should be comfortable writing complex T-SQL queries / stored procedures to feed these reports.
  • Power BI Mastery: Expert knowledge of Power BI Desktop and Power BI Service (Admin). Proficiency in DAX and Power Query (M) is essential.
  • Database Skills: Strong proficiency in SQL (T-SQL) for data extraction and a solid understanding of relational database structures (SQL Server / Azure SQL).

Soft Skills

  • Queue Management: Ability to prioritize and manage a backlog of reporting requests independently.
  • Attention to Detail: A "perfectionist" mindset when it comes to data accuracy and visual alignment.
  • Communication: Ability to explain data trends and technical limitations to non-technical business users.

Time Zone: Must be located in or able to work consistently within the EST time zone (9:00 AM - 5:00 PM) to ensure synchronized collaboration with our national teams.


The Reward

The A-Team: Work alongside high-performing talent in the industry.

Accelerated Growth: The slope of your learning curve here will be vertical. You will touch more production systems in one year than you would in five years at a bank.

Best-in-Class Tools: Access to the resources and tech you need to execute without friction.

Working framework: the environment that makes you productive and enables teamwork.




Diversity & Inclusion

At nesto, we believe that creativity and collaboration are the result of a diverse team. We are committed to fostering a culture of diversity, equity, inclusion, and belonging, and we strongly encourage women, people of color, LGBTQIA+ individuals, and individuals with disabilities to apply. We are committed to creating a workplace that is inclusive and welcoming to all.¬†

Maintain relationships and directly interface with third party data providers to onboard and update content successfully.

Who you are:

Education

  • Completion of Undergraduate Degree

Experience

  • 4+ years of relevant experience at a software (GIS) or data company.
