Title: Senior Data Analyst

Employee Working Location: Partially Virtual / Hybrid (Canada)

Employment Status: Permanent Full-time

¬†

The Canadian Red Cross (Red Cross) ‚Äì an inspirational not for profit organization, helps people and communities in Canada and around the world in times of need and supports them in strengthening their resilience. As a Canada‚Äôs Best Employers 2024, we are committed to having an accessible, diverse, inclusive, and barrier-free work environment. ¬†

The Senior Data Analyst plays a critical role in driving data-informed decision-making by performing advanced data analysis, developing reports, and optimizing data processes. This position works with large datasets, designs dashboards and other visualizations, and provides analytics results to support business strategies. They collaborate with cross-functional teams, ensure data quality, provide meaningful insights, and contribute to the development of best practices in data management and analytics.

¬†

In this role you will:

  • Qualifications include a minimum of 6-9 years experience and a 3-year college diploma or university degree and/or an equivalent combination of education and experience. May require a graduate diploma/degree in a related field and/or a professional degree, certification, or designation. Requires expertise in a specialized discipline or broad experience across fields, along with an understanding of interconnections between processes and business units.

  • Proficiency in Python specifically for data manipulation, ETL automation, and processing large flat-file datasets (e.g., Pandas)

  • Advanced proficiency in Power BI, including strong skills in Power Query (M) for data transformation and DAX for measure creation.

  • Demonstrated experience establishing data governance frameworks, including creating data dictionaries, SOPs, and data quality standards.

  • Understanding of ETL (Extract, Transform, Load) processes, specifically automating data pipelines from file-based sources (CSV, Excel, API exports) to reporting tools.

  • Proficiency in standard computer applications (Microsoft Office Suite) and Excel (macros, VBA).

  • Strong understanding of relational data modeling and database concepts.

  • Ability to act as a technical mentor to junior analysts, specifically regarding documentation and coding best practices.

  • Communication and influence skills to gather perspectives, understand needs, and present information to reach consensus, often in somewhat sensitive situations.

  • Ability to identify complex problems, analyze interrelated factors, assess and mitigate risks, and develop solutions using specialized skills.

  • Proficiency in SQL is considered an asset.

¬†

What we are looking for:

  • Collaborate with leaders to identify data requirements and ensure data deliverables are accurate, efficient and align with business objectives.

  • Act as a data ambassador, promoting a data-driven culture across the organization and implementing best practices for data governance, data quality assurance, and documentation based on established organizational standards

  • Create and maintain accurate and up-to-date documentation of data processes, requirements, and specifications.

  • Perform source system data analysis in order to manage source to target data mapping and ensure that mapping is up to date.

  • Build relationships with clients and partners and collaborate to identify and solve problems and implement solutions. ¬† ¬†

  • Design and implement data-driven solutions to optimize processes, performance and leverage technology.

  • Identify opportunities for continuous improvement and provide recommendations to automate data processes, improve quality and efficiency.

  • Apply advanced analytical techniques to identify trends, insights, and areas for improvement.

  • Develop sophisticated visualizations and dashboards to communicate data insights to stakeholders and make data accessible.

  • Lead and coordinate data analysis, reporting, and audit activities for assigned clients or projects

  • Collaborate to rationalize and standardize cross-platform data analysis.

  • Support the development of performance indicators.

  • Actively participates in and contributes to data governance and management forum.

¬†

Working Conditions : ¬†

  • As we work with and support people (managers, colleagues, beneficiaries/customers, volunteers, donors and external partners) and communities in Canada and around the world, applicants whose first language is not English may be required to perform the responsibilities of the role in English. ¬†

  • Eligibility to work in Canada: At this time, we welcome applications from candidates eligible to work in Canada. If you are not a citizen or permanent resident of Canada, we encourage you to carefully review your visa to find out whether you are eligible to work in the job you are considering applying for. Refer to our FAQ for more information. ¬†

  • If you are selected for this role, you will be required to complete a successful pre-employment screening process which includes a satisfactory Enhanced Police Information Check (E-PIC). ¬†¬†

job_information.title: Financial Data Analyst
job_information.description:
WHO WE ARE ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬†

HomeEquity Bank is a Schedule 1 Canadian chartered bank and the leading national provider of reverse mortgages, with a growing portfolio. As the only bank solely dedicated to serving homeowners 55 and up, we‚Äôre passionate about helping Canadian homeowners live retirement on their terms. We live that commitment every day, with a range of reverse mortgage solutions that include our flagship CHIP Reverse Mortgage‚Ñ¢ product. ¬†
¬†¬†

OUR VALUES, OUR PASSION

At HomeEquity Bank, our values drive and inspire our actions with our customers, our partners and each other. ¬†

  • Customer-Focused. Passionate Advocates¬†
  • Courage to Act. Do the Right Thing¬†
  • One Team. One Vision¬†
  • Think Long-Term. Ever-Evolving¬†
  • Be Exceptional. Inspire Greatness

POSITION SUMMARY
¬†

The role is a critical member of the Finance team and will assist developing, updating and maintaining platforms, models and procedures used in the financial results of HomeEquity Bank (the Bank). The tools include those relating to accounting, reporting, treasury, capital and underwriting. It will combine accounting knowledge and data analyst skills to support efficiency and accuracy with the preparation of monthly results providing detailed analysis thereof.

The role utilizes the Finance intranet site which incorporates the Bank‚Äôs mortgage information and external market information. The intranet site, underlying database tables, and models are used by multiple departments across the Bank supplying detailed information on the mortgage portfolio and monthly mortgage activity.

MAJOR ELEMENTS OF THE ROLE
¬†

Database management

  • Assist with the creation and maintenance of the database housing the details of the mortgage portfolio.

  • Maintain the database to HEB‚Äôs standards for controls including user access, data integrity and performance.

  • Deploy data analyst skillset to manage efficiency in the functionally of reports, complex calculations and queries received from executives and others.

OSFI Mortgage Risk Weighting

  • Maintain an understanding of the OSFI CAR Guideline for the Capital Risk Weight to be applied to the mortgage portfolio.

  • Incorporate changes and updates to the Guidelines as required. Provide detailed analysis of the impact of the updates.

  • Maintain documentation of the process and calculations.

  • Maintain stress testing models for ICAAP including the development of geographic regions with differing stress testing assumptions. This aspect of the role requires liaising with members of the Treasury Department.

IFRS ECL Reserves

  • Obtain a thorough understanding of the IFRS 9 requirements for the Bank‚Äôs mortgage reserves.

  • Support the maintenance of the IFRS ECL methodology:

    • Mortgage by mortgage assessment;

    • Review the integrity of underwriting assumptions used by the ECL methodology in the Bank‚Äôs mortgage enterprise system (MARS);

    • Utilization of the Bank‚Äôs Cash Flow model;

    • Assessment of future interest rates and property appreciation rates.

  • Incorporate and maintain the forward-looking information into the calculations.

  • Perform detailed analysis and run stress-testing scenarios to support monthly ECL results.

  • Provide detailed analysis of the impact of changes as needed based on proposed amendments to the methodology.

  • Maintain documentation of the process and calculations.

Real Estate Market

  • Keep abreast of the Canadian real estate market activity, home sales, sale prices, etc.

  • Capture and incorporate CREA monthly real estate market activity into the ECL methodology.

  • Maintain and align funded data with real estate boards at the city/FSA level.

  • Provide market analysis in the assessment of the mortgage portfolio LTVs and resulting reserves.

Cross Department Support

  • Maintain reports and queries supporting other department requests.

  • Support Client Relations, Operations, Risk, IT, Marketing when required ‚Äì support issues on mortgage balances and activity, interest calculations, re-appraisal requirements.

Enterprise Support

  • Respond to ad-hoc query requests from end-users and to user requests for data changes/corrections.

SKILLS AND EXPERIENCE REQUIRED
¬†

Qualifications

  • University Degree and 5 years+ experience in a Canadian financial institution working in an analytical capacity.

  • Bachelor‚Äôs degree in data analysis or statistics or similar formal studies that developed an educational foundation in accounting, finance, economics or mathematics.

  • Familiar with the syntax and application of languages such as C#, Transact SQL and VB.NET.

  • Preference given to a knowledge of ASP.NET tools. Knowledge of Telerik controls preferred.

  • Knowledge of source code tracking tools and development tools such as Visual Studio and Team Foundation Server is an asset.

  • A working knowledge of Python and select modules used in the reading and uploading of large data files.

  • Experienced in writing complex SQL queries to retrieve information from relational databases.

  • Experienced in presenting information to end users using a variety of tools such MS Excel and browsers.

  • Familiar with financial concepts such as, but not limited to, mortgages, simple interest, compound interest, property appraisals, weighting, payments of principal and interest,, ¬†and related concepts.

Working conditions unique to job

  • Hybrid work environment

WHY WORK AT HOMEEQUITY BANK?

Great Environment

HomeEquity Bank offers a hybrid working environment supported with a culture of flexibility ‚Äì an approach that is unique to each person, and that enables both business and individual needs to be met in a mutually beneficial way.

job_information.title: Senior Data Analyst
job_information.description:
Title: Senior Data Analyst

Employee Working Location: Partially Virtual / Hybrid (Canada)

Employment Status: Permanent Full-time

¬†

The Canadian Red Cross (Red Cross) ‚Äì an inspirational not for profit organization, helps people and communities in Canada and around the world in times of need and supports them in strengthening their resilience. As a Canada‚Äôs Best Employers 2024, we are committed to having an accessible, diverse, inclusive, and barrier-free work environment. ¬†

The Senior Data Analyst plays a critical role in driving data-informed decision-making by performing advanced data analysis, developing reports, and optimizing data processes. This position works with large datasets, designs dashboards and other visualizations, and provides analytics results to support business strategies. They collaborate with cross-functional teams, ensure data quality, provide meaningful insights, and contribute to the development of best practices in data management and analytics.

¬†

In this role you will:

  • Qualifications include a minimum of 6-9 years experience and a 3-year college diploma or university degree and/or an equivalent combination of education and experience. May require a graduate diploma/degree in a related field and/or a professional degree, certification, or designation. Requires expertise in a specialized discipline or broad experience across fields, along with an understanding of interconnections between processes and business units.

  • Proficiency in Python specifically for data manipulation, ETL automation, and processing large flat-file datasets (e.g., Pandas)

  • Advanced proficiency in Power BI, including strong skills in Power Query (M) for data transformation and DAX for measure creation.

  • Demonstrated experience establishing data governance frameworks, including creating data dictionaries, SOPs, and data quality standards.

  • Understanding of ETL (Extract, Transform, Load) processes, specifically automating data pipelines from file-based sources (CSV, Excel, API exports) to reporting tools.

  • Proficiency in standard computer applications (Microsoft Office Suite) and Excel (macros, VBA).

  • Strong understanding of relational data modeling and database concepts.

  • Ability to act as a technical mentor to junior analysts, specifically regarding documentation and coding best practices.

  • Communication and influence skills to gather perspectives, understand needs, and present information to reach consensus, often in somewhat sensitive situations.

  • Ability to identify complex problems, analyze interrelated factors, assess and mitigate risks, and develop solutions using specialized skills.

  • Proficiency in SQL is considered an asset.

¬†

What we are looking for:

  • Collaborate with leaders to identify data requirements and ensure data deliverables are accurate, efficient and align with business objectives.

  • Act as a data ambassador, promoting a data-driven culture across the organization and implementing best practices for data governance, data quality assurance, and documentation based on established organizational standards

  • Create and maintain accurate and up-to-date documentation of data processes, requirements, and specifications.

  • Perform source system data analysis in order to manage source to target data mapping and ensure that mapping is up to date.

  • Build relationships with clients and partners and collaborate to identify and solve problems and implement solutions. ¬† ¬†

  • Design and implement data-driven solutions to optimize processes, performance and leverage technology.

  • Identify opportunities for continuous improvement and provide recommendations to automate data processes, improve quality and efficiency.

  • Apply advanced analytical techniques to identify trends, insights, and areas for improvement.

  • Develop sophisticated visualizations and dashboards to communicate data insights to stakeholders and make data accessible.

  • Lead and coordinate data analysis, reporting, and audit activities for assigned clients or projects

  • Collaborate to rationalize and standardize cross-platform data analysis.

  • Support the development of performance indicators.

  • Actively participates in and contributes to data governance and management forum.

¬†

Working Conditions : ¬†

  • As we work with and support people (managers, colleagues, beneficiaries/customers, volunteers, donors and external partners) and communities in Canada and around the world, applicants whose first language is not English may be required to perform the responsibilities of the role in English. ¬†

  • Eligibility to work in Canada: At this time, we welcome applications from candidates eligible to work in Canada. If you are not a citizen or permanent resident of Canada, we encourage you to carefully review your visa to find out whether you are eligible to work in the job you are considering applying for. Refer to our FAQ for more information. ¬†

  • If you are selected for this role, you will be required to complete a successful pre-employment screening process which includes a satisfactory Enhanced Police Information Check (E-PIC). ¬†¬†

job_information.description:
Who we are is what we do.

Deel is the all-in-one payroll and HR platform for global teams. Our vision is to unlock global opportunity for every person, team, and business. Built for the way the world works today, Deel combines HRIS, payroll, compliance, benefits, performance, and equipment management into one seamless platform. With AI-powered tools and a fully owned payroll infrastructure, Deel supports every worker type in 150+ countries‚Äîhelping businesses scale smarter, faster, and more compliantly.

Among the largest globally distributed companies in the world, our team of 7,000 spans more than 100 countries, speaks 74 languages, and brings a connected and dynamic culture that drives continuous learning and innovation for our customers.

Why should you be part of our success story?

As the fastest-growing Software as a Service (SaaS) company in history, Deel is transforming how global talent connects with world-class companies ‚Äì breaking down borders that have traditionally limited both hiring and career opportunities. We're not just building software; we're creating the infrastructure for the future of work, enabling a more diverse and inclusive global economy. In 2024 alone, we paid $11.2 billion to workers in nearly 100 currencies and provided healthcare and benefits to workers in 109 countries‚Äîensuring people get paid and protected, no matter where they are.

Our momentum is reflected in our achievements and customer satisfaction: CNBC Disruptor 50,¬† Forbes Cloud 100, Deloitte Fast 500, and repeated recognition on Y Combinator‚Äôs top companies list ‚Äì all while maintaining a 4.83 average rating from 15,000 reviews across G2, Trustpilot, Captera, Apple and Google.

Your experience at Deel will be a career accelerator. At the forefront of the global work revolution, you'll tackle complex challenges that impact millions of people's working lives. With our momentum‚Äîbacked by a $17.3 billion valuation and $1 B¬†in Annual Recurring Revenue (ARR) in just over five years‚Äîyou'll drive meaningful impact while building expertise that makes you a sought-after leader in the transformation of global work.

About the role

Deel is one of the fastest SaaS companies ever to reach 100M revenue, and is far along the way to become the fastest company to $1B revenue. Driven by an enormous market, and high speed of innovation, Deel has expanded their product suite and customer base by many orders of magnitude in the last few years. With over 20,000 global customers, customer success is a vital strategic pillar for Deel. As Senior Analyst for Sales, you‚Äôll work closely with Sales leadership and teams across the globe, helping them sell our products more effectively.

Responsibilities

  • As part of our data team, you‚Äôll work closely with data engineers, analytics engineers and analysts across the business to develop our tools.¬†

  • You‚Äôll work closely with the most senior Sales stakeholders¬†

  • You will drive the direction of our sales performance and forecasting data models and reporting infrastructure, building dashboards in Looker¬†

  • You will support data enrichment of our Sales tools, to ensure Sales Reps have the right insights at their disposal where they do their work.¬†¬†

  • You‚Äôll own the definition, quality and reliability for key Sales metrics, like Quota attainments and Sales pipeline funnel.¬†

  • Working closely with analytics engineering, you‚Äôll help evolve our dbt model infrastructure¬†

  • You‚Äôll collaborate closely with our data science teams to refine forecasting models

  • You‚Äôll build reporting in Looker, from highly curated and formatted dashboards that will see 1000+ viewers per months, to highly customizable self-service frameworks for specific stakeholders¬†

Requirements:

  • You hold a Bachelor‚Äôs degree in Math, Economics, CS, or another STEM field

  • You have at least 5 years experience in an analytical role¬†

  • You‚Äôre an excellent communicator, you know how to tell simple, but compelling stories with data

  • You work well with people across the spectrum¬†

  • Highly proficient in SQL¬†

  • Experience in data visualization tooling (we use Looker)

  • Some experience in data modeling and metrics design


We'd especially love to speak with you if:

  • You have a worked with dbt and LookML

  • You have experience using Sales platforms like Salesforce, Gong or Outreach¬†

  • Experience with version control tools (GitHub, GitLab)

  • You‚Äôve worked for fast-growing B2B SaaS companies

  • You have experience with commercial domains, like Revenue Operations, Sales Ops, or Customer Success.

Total Rewards

Our workforce deserves fair and competitive pay that meets them where they are. With scalable benefits, rewards, and perks, our total rewards programs reflect our commitment to inclusivity and access for all.¬†

Some things you‚Äôll enjoy

  • Stock grant opportunities dependent on your role, employment status and location

  • Additional perks and benefits based on your employment status and country

  • The flexibility of remote work, including optional WeWork access

At Deel, we‚Äôre an equal-opportunity employer that values diversity and positively encourage applications from suitably qualified and eligible candidates regardless of¬† race, religion, sex, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, disability status, pregnancy or maternity or other applicable legally protected characteristics.

Unless otherwise agreed, we will communicate with job applicants using Deel-specific emails, which include @deel.com and other acquired company emails like @payspace.com and @paygroup.com. You can view the most up-to-date job listings at Deel by visiting our careers page.

Deel is an equal-opportunity employer and is committed to cultivating a diverse and inclusive workplace that reflects different abilities, backgrounds, beliefs, experiences, identities and perspectives.

Deel will provide accommodations on request throughout the recruitment, selection and assessment process for applicants with disabilities. If you require accommodations, please inform our Talent Acquisition Team via this link and a team member will be in touch to ensure your equal participation. If you have difficulty accessing the form, please email at recruiting@deel.com.

For positions in New York City, our use of Covey complies with NYC Local Law 144.

We began using Covey Scout for Inbound on March 30, 2025.

job_information.description:
Senior Data Analyst

Department: Member Experience and Pension Operations

Type: 18-Month Contract

Location: Toronto (Hybrid)

Posting Date: January 5, 2026.

At OPTrust, paying pensions today, preserving pensions for tomorrow is our mission and business.

When you choose OPTrust, you join a team of smart, talented people who fuel our success and have a passion for pensions. Everyone at OPTrust ‚Äì in Toronto, London and Sydney ‚Äì makes a meaningful impact. Our culture is driven by team members with different backgrounds and perspectives, creating an inclusive and fulfilling place to work for everyone. We work in a fast-paced environment, but we find time to have fun and give back to the community.

What OPTrust Offers You

  • Unique culture rooted in our core values ‚Äì collaboration and teamwork, integrity, respect, flexibility, excellence and continuous improvement.¬†

  • A purpose-driven environment where we all work towards the common goal of paying pensions today and preserving pensions for tomorrow.¬†

  • A flexible, hybrid work model.¬†

  • Benefits package after six months of consecutive employment.

  • Optional membership in our world-class defined benefit pension plan.¬†

  • A dedicated inclusion, diversity and equity strategy with meaningful opportunities to participate, including our employee-led resource groups.¬†

About the role

This role is accountable for delivering technical expertise and contributing to the development and maintenance of data management practices.¬† The mandate includes designing and implementing business processes, systems, methods and procedures that ensure accurate reconciliation, strong controls, and a high standard of quality and integrity for employer and plan member information. ¬†In addition, this position is responsible for building and maintaining reporting solutions using business intelligence tools, enabling actionable insights and informed decision-making across the organisation.

What you‚Äôll do

1. Provide expertise on business intelligence and data management standards, business process operating methods, and work procedures. Examples of key tasks include:

  • Build and prepare statistical reports and/or presentations on results, findings, and recommendations related to business process reviews and ongoing data management functions, identifying and documenting trends in data problems and passing on information and suggestions regarding improved data handling and control to the manager.

  • Provide support to product owners by generating and presenting data in a form that assists with business decisions (trends, projections, volumes, etc.).

  • Work with datasets by extracting, transforming, organising, and translating raw data into actionable insight, data workflow, and work-inventory management for the department to maintain service levels, productivity, and standards.

  • Analyse and establish internal work processes, procedures, and controls related to the entire cycle of data interface processing and reconciliation.

  • Follow up with OPTrust staff and employers to resolve data processing and reconciliation problems, including source file issues, membership and contribution split reconciliations, problem-solving of aborted updates of the pension database, and recovery implementation.

  • Represent OPTrust in discussions with employers regarding OPTrust data control and integrity requirements.

  • Follow up and assist employers in reviewing work processes and procedures related to member data.

  • Detect and implement solutions to complex data integrity issues with employers and OPTrust business areas.

  • Design and deliver presentations, education, and training to employer representatives or OPTrust staff regarding data management processes, systems, and procedures.

  • Develop and support initiatives in achieving departmental benchmarks and goals.

  • Work with individual smaller employers/payroll providers to improve their extract programmes to meet OPTrust‚Äôs requirements.

  • Develop structured testing of data received to improve business processes.

  • Develop audit programmes to validate the data received from employers.

  • Lead the batch data remediation processes for batch extracts, including Annual Pension Statement (APS).

  • Support generating remediation information for the Annual Valuation Extract (AVE) purposes to reduce remedial process time.

  • Perform annual update and verification of system tables.

2. Represent the data management group in special project work teams related to the design testing and implementation of new system applications as well as annual project deliverables. Examples of key tasks include:

  • Provide business analysis from a data management perspective on projects regarding member- and employer-data-related controls and completeness and accuracy of such data; projects cover areas such as data purification, production of accurate annual pension statements to members, extraction of actuarial data, and maintenance of pension records and benefits for members on long-term disability.

  • Analyse data management user requirements related to new application development.

  • Participate in system design walkthroughs and evaluations.

  • Develop user acceptance test plans, including test strategy, test criteria, and test data identification, resources, and time estimates; implement and control user acceptance test projects, identifying issues with IT as needed.

  • Control code table administration for the pension database and security requests for special project users.

  • Design and deliver training and support to users of the pension database and coordinate database communication updates.

What you bring

  • Advanced knowledge of pension plan administration and of related legislation/plan provisions, including the OPSEU Pension Plan text, the Pension Benefits Act, the Family Law Act, and federal statutes such as CPP, EI, and the Income Tax Act.¬†

  • Applied knowledge of business and administrative processes and systems in the financial services sector.

  • Familiar with extracting, transforming, and loading (ETL) methods for large datasets, integrating source data to produce actionable insights.

  • Knowledge of electronic data processing and financial system controls and methods to establish operating procedures that ensure control and integrity of data management processes.

  • Knowledge of database systems operations and use, spreadsheet applications, and database inquiry languages and products to resolve complex data problems, redesign work processes/procedures, and provide technical assistance/guidance to junior staff.

  • Experience using MS Office Suite (Excel, PowerPoint, Power BI).

  • Post-secondary degree or diploma.¬†

  • Experience with database systems operations.

  • Experience building dashboards using Microsoft Power BI or Tableau.

  • Familiar with SQL and writing scripts to extract data.

  • Experience with RPA or other automation development is highly preferred.

  • Strong research and analytical skills to identify and resolve complex membership data problems and improve operating/control procedures and efficiency and make related recommendations.

  • Strong organisational skills to balance workload and set priorities.

  • Excellent written and verbal communication skills.

  • Interpersonal and negotiation skills along with a strong client service orientation.

  • Positive attitude towards work and colleagues to support team goals and organization values of strong teamwork, cooperation and mutual respect.

  • High degree of accountability and personal leadership.

Please submit your application via Workday by January 26, 2026.

job_information.title: IT Compliance Analyst
job_information.description:
At Stantec, we have some of the world‚Äôs leading professionals passionate about enabling our business to be its best. Our business teams include finance, procurement, human resources, information technology, marketing, corporate development, HSSE, real estate, legal, and practice services. We bring diverse backgrounds, skills, and expertise and create a caring culture where everyone can thrive. Through teamwork and collaboration, we‚Äôre building a stronger, more resilient Stantec every day.‚ÄØ‚ÄØ‚ÄØ‚ÄØ 

Your Opportunity 

Are you someone who loves structure, finds satisfaction in completing checklists, and has a knack for keeping things organized and accurate? As an IT Compliance Analyst, you‚Äôll play a key role in keeping our systems audit-ready by coordinating documentation, managing recurring control tasks, and supporting ISO/IEC 20000 and IT General Controls (ITGC) processes.  You‚Äôll work in a well-defined, collaborative environment alongside experienced compliance professionals - gaining hands-on exposure to how enterprise IT compliance works in practice. If you're looking to grow your skills in a role where attention to detail and reliability truly matter, this is a great step toward a future in compliance, audit support, or IT service operations.

Your Key Responsibilities

  • Coordinate user access review cycles by managing schedules, sending follow-up reminders, tracking completion, and compiling evidence packages for senior compliance review.
  • Collect and organize documentation for recurring control activities ‚Äî including change management and major incident reconciliations ‚Äî ensuring completeness and consistency.
  • Generate standard system reports (e.g., ConfigSnapshot) using approved templates and set parameters, with no analysis or interpretation required.
  • Maintain compliance tracking systems and structured document libraries through consistent file labeling, data entry, and basic quality checks.
  • Prepare audit-ready documentation packages by verifying file formats, naming conventions, and completeness ahead of internal or external reviews.
  • Update compliance dashboards and activity logs with factual task status, key dates, and reference links.
  • Provide administrative support for compliance operations, including scheduling meetings, managing calendar milestones, and distributing procedural communications.
  • Conduct quality assurance reviews of documentation for format and completeness before escalating to senior staff.

Qualifications

Your Capabilities and Credentials

Required:

  • Strong organizational and coordination skills ‚Äî comfortable managing checklists, schedules, and multiple administrative workflows.
  • High attention to detail ‚Äî especially when handling files, reviewing records, and logging data accurately.
  • Proficiency in Microsoft Excel and SharePoint ‚Äî confident navigating folders, inputting data, and using basic templates.
  • Clear and professional communication ‚Äî able to follow up with stakeholders and provide precise status updates.
  • Ability to follow structured procedures with minimal supervision ‚Äî comfortable working within set guidelines.
  • Awareness of confidentiality and data handling best practices.

Preferred:

  • Familiarity with ITGCs (e.g., access, change, backups) and/or IT service management standards like ISO/IEC 20000 or ITIL.
  • Previous experience supporting compliance or audit-driven environments (e.g., SOX, ISO audits).

Time Zone: Must be located in or able to work consistently within the EST time zone (9:00 AM - 5:00 PM) to ensure synchronized collaboration with our national teams.

job_information.title: Senior Data Governance Analyst
job_information.description:
At Trisura, we expect more because we believe it can be done better.

 

We are a young, growth oriented team with a commitment to exceptional talent and have been named one of Canada’s Top Small and Medium Employers since 2017. Our growth and our entrepreneurial style, niche market position and development opportunities ensure that our people see the results of their commitment reflected in the company’s success.

We are currently seeking a driven and collaborative Senior Data Governance Analyst to join our forward-thinking information systems team in our downtown Toronto office.

 

SENIOR DATA GOVERNANCE ANALYST – TORONTO

 

Position Overview:

 

As a Senior Data Governance Analyst on our Data & Analytics Team, you’ll play a vital role in ensuring that data is accurate, consistent, and trusted across the business. This role goes beyond compliance, you will help shape how our data is governed, making it easier to share, analyze, and leverage across the organization. You’ll collaborate with business and technical partners to design governance practices that directly impact decision-making, support advanced analytics, and prepare us for innovative uses of data in the insurance industry.

 

Working alongside skilled colleagues in engineering, finance, actuarial, and operations, you’ll ensure that our data is high-quality and AI-ready, helping unlock new insights and improve business performance. If you’re passionate about data, eager to make an impact, and ready to grow your career in a collaborative and high-performance culture, this opportunity is for you.

 

What you will do:.

 

  • Strategic Data Governance Leadership: Design and implement enterprise data governance policies, standards, and best practices that scale with our growth.
  • Data Quality: Build and maintain SQL-driven validation checks and automated profiling processes to safeguard accuracy and reliability.
  • Metadata & Lineage: Maintain the enterprise data dictionary, lineage documentation, and standardized definitions.
  • AI & Analytics Support: Collaborate with Data Science teams to provide governed, high-quality, and unbiased data for AI and advanced analytics. Implement AI governance controls such as lineage tracking, versioning, and explainability.
  • Collaboration: Partner with Finance, Operations, Actuarial, and IT teams to address governance challenges and standardize practices.
  • Subject Matter Expertise: Act as a data governance expert with internal teams and external partners, including regulators, to promote secure, effective, and collaborative data sharing across the insurance ecosystem.
  • Continuous Improvement: Stay current with evolving governance, data quality, and AI frameworks, bringing new ideas and practices to the organization.
  • Data Remediation: Develop SQL queries to analyze datasets and correct data integration data failures.
  • Adhoc SQL tasks: Execute SQL templated tasks to implement accounting functionalities (reversals, re-invoicing) whilst ensuring data consistency.

 

 

What You Bring:

 

Core Skills:

  • Strong SQL coding skills with the ability to write clear, efficient, and well-documented code.
  • Proven experience in data governance and data quality management.
  • Strong communication skills to bridge technical concepts with business needs.
  • Ability to manage priorities in a fast-paced, evolving environment.
  • Curiosity, attention to detail, and passion for data-driven decision-making.

 

 

Technical Expertise:

  • Advanced T-SQL development (queries, stored procedures, optimization).
  • Experience with enterprise metadata management platforms (Purview, Collibra, or similar).
  • Azure MS Power Platform (Power BI, PowerApps, Power Automate) exposure.
  • Experience with AI/ML workflows (data preparation, feature engineering, evaluation) is an asset.

 

Qualifications:

  • Bachelor’s degree or college diploma in Information Management, Computer Science, Data Science or related field.
  • Minimum 5 years of overall professional experience, including at least 2 years in data governance, or data management role.
  • Strong SQL development experience (T-SQL preferred).
  • Knowledge of data warehousing concepts and ETL processes.
  • Familiarity with AI governance principles and ethical AI practices an asset.
  • Strong analytical and problem-solving skills with a keen eye for detail.
  • Relevant certifications such as Certified Data Management Professional (CDMP) or Certified Information Privacy Professional (CIPP) are considered assets.
  • Prior work experience in insurance, financial services, or other regulated industries is an advantage.

 

Why Join Us:

  • Work for a recognized leader in the insurance industry with a culture that values innovation, collaboration, and excellence.
  • Play a key role in shaping the future of data governance and AI governance.
  • Enjoy a flexible hybrid work model that balances work and life.
  • Access professional development and career growth opportunities.
  • See your work make a real impact, our entrepreneurial style means your contributions are visible and celebrated.

 

Compensation:

  • The expected compensation in this position is within the range of $90,000 - $110,000

 

This position is for an existing, currently vacant position.

 

#LI-Hybrid 

If you are looking for a career in an exciting and rewarding company, are driven to excel, thrive in a team environment and want to contribute to the success of an organization that values your contribution, we would like to hear from you!

We are committed to an inclusive and barrier-free workplace that reflects the diversity in each of our offices across Canada. Accommodations will be provided on request for candidates taking part in all aspects of our recruitment and selection process.

We thank all candidates for their interest however only those selected for an interview will be contacted.

Trisura, headquartered in the heart of Canada’s financial district, is a specialty lines insurer with a focus on Surety, Specialty Insurance, Property & Casualty, and Warranty products.
 
Trisura brings innovative solutions and expertise through a select network of both national and regional brokerage firms. 
 
The company, founded in 2006, and operating across North America with offices in Toronto, Ottawa, Halifax, Montréal, Calgary, Vancouver, Stamford. Denver, Chicago, Philadelphia and Oklahoma City, is uniquely positioned to satisfy all varieties of risk in Contract, Commercial and Developer Surety, Directors' and Officers' Liability, Fidelity, and Professional Liability including Media Liability, as well as Warranty products.

job_information.description:
Senior Data Analyst and Engineer (ArcGIS) 

Location: Remote with ability to travel up to 50% to Colorado * Clearance: Ability to attain a Public Trust Clearance  


Position Overview
We are seeking a Senior Data Analyst and Engineer with deep expertise in ArcGIS and geospatial data systems to design, build, and maintain advanced data processing pipelines for enterprise-level GIS initiatives. This role will focus on capturing requirements, architecting geospatial databases, executing complex data migrations, and documenting all processes to ensure compliance with federal and organizational standards. The ideal candidate will have strong skills in SQL, Python, and PowerShell, along with extensive experience leveraging ArcGIS Data Interoperability and related ETL tools to manage spatial and non-spatial datasets. 


Highlights of working for Quevera are:

Quevera employees voted Quevera as a TOP EMPLOYER in the Baltimore /DC area for 2020 (ranked #8 out of 150 companies) and 2022 (ranked #5 out of 150 companies).

•             Yearly $5,000 towards education/training.

•             Employees are in control of their career path through our Career Pathway Program.

•             Family and corporate events

•             Excellent health care coverage (100% paid premium option) and 401K matching (up to 4%).

•             And many more!

•             Q-Culture Video

•             Q-Careers


Key Responsibilities
Develop and maintain data processing pipelines and workflows for geospatial data integration using ArcGIS Enterprise, ArcGIS Pro, and ArcGIS Online.
Design and optimize database schemas, including enterprise geodatabases, to support spatial data storage, retrieval, and analysis.
Capture and analyze data requirements from stakeholders, translating them into actionable engineering solutions.
Perform data migration and transformation using ETL tools such as ArcGIS Data Interoperability, SQL Server Integration Services (SSIS), and open-source frameworks.
Ensure geospatial data quality, integrity, and compliance with federal metadata and governance standards (FGDC, ISO 19115).
Document data architectures, pipeline workflows, and integration processes for operational transparency and maintainability.
Collaborate with cross-functional teams, including GIS analysts, developers, and business users, to deliver scalable data solutions.
Support the development of automated geoprocessing scripts and data validation tools in Python and PowerShell to streamline workflows.
Provide guidance on best practices for managing geospatial data in enterprise environments and mentor junior team members. 

Required Qualifications
Bachelor’s degree in Geographic Information Systems (GIS), Data Engineering, Computer Science, or a related technical discipline.
Minimum of 5 years’ experience in data analysis and engineering, with significant work focused on geospatial data systems.
Proficiency in ArcGIS platforms, including ArcGIS Pro, ArcGIS Enterprise, and ArcGIS Online.
Hands-on experience with ETL processes and tools such as ArcGIS Data Interoperability, SSIS, and Python-based frameworks.
Strong skills in SQL, Python, and PowerShell for data management and automation.
Experience designing and managing enterprise geodatabases and integrating spatial and non-spatial data.
Excellent documentation, analytical, and communication skills to convey technical concepts to diverse stakeholders. 

Preferred Qualifications
Experience working in federal data governance frameworks or other highly regulated environments.
Familiarity with cloud-hosted geospatial data environments (e.g., ArcGIS Enterprise on AWS/Azure).
Knowledge of advanced spatial analytics, geoprocessing, and metadata management.
Relevant certifications such as GISP (GIS Professional) or Esri Technical Certifications. 

 

Quevera is an equal opportunity/affirmative action employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to sex, gender identity, sexual orientation, race, color, religion, national origin, disability, protected veteran status, age or any other characteristic protected by law

English Job Description:

The Senior Data Analyst I, Product within Mistplay's Data department will play a crucial role in enhancing Mistplay's business performance through insightful analysis and driving analytics strategy. Reporting to the Manager of Data Analytics & Experimentation, you will collaborate with Product & Lifecycle Managers to plan and analyze the results of A/B tests and engagement campaigns targeting various aspects of the user lifecycle, and drive insights reporting in order to inform the release of new product features and engagement strategies.


What You'll Be Doing:
Conduct proactive analysis to identify actionable insights, including diving into the core product funnel, user cohorts, and analyzing user behaviour data, in order to identify areas of the user experience that can be improved to drive new business opportunities.
Define KPIs for the company and build automated dashboards, reports, and models to enable teams at Mistplay to make better decisions.
Design, orchestrate, and analyze the results of multivariate product experiments to help drive growth, improve existing product features, and test new areas of opportunity.
Collaborate with data, product, marketing, and engineering stakeholders to define business problems, scope out projects, identify risks and dependencies, and create execution plans.

What We're Looking For:
BA/BS in Computer Science, Math, Economics, Statistics, or other quantitative fields
3-4 years of work experience doing quantitative analysis (preferably in the tech industry) and a proven track record of impacting a business or product decisions
Pro-level ability to synthesize and communicate complex concepts and analyses in simple, easy-to-understand ways, to a wide range of technical and non-technical audiences
Familiarity with online lifecycle marketing concepts, including email, push notifications, and attribution strategies.
Past experience in A/B testing, and a strong foundational knowledge of core inferential statistics concepts (significance, power, confidence intervals, variance, etc.)
Fluency in SQL. Experience pulling highly dimensional and complex data, as well as modeling scenarios and sensitivity analysis using Excel
Experience with Python or another programming tool for statistical modeling
Familiarity with Tableau or any BI tool 
Familiarity with cloud data technologies such as AWS, Azure, or Databricks to query and build data models and reports 
Positive attitude and a healthy dose of natural curiosity. Questions have to be answered and our data isn't just going to analyze itself. (We're working on that.)

Bonus if you have:
A love of gaming and familiarity with the games industry
Understanding of data science and machine learning techniques
Experience working with very large data sets and distributed computing (Hive/Hadoop)
Experience working with multichannel marketing platforms such as Braze


We work hard to make our work atmosphere as inviting and fun as possible! Working at Mistplay is coupled with a whole array of perks that we've adopted virtually and in-person: Team Lunches, game nights, company-wide events, and so much more. 

Our culture is deeply rooted in growth and upheld by a team of smart, dynamic, and enthusiastic people. We utilize data to constantly learn, improve, and adapt. We foster an environment where everyone is encouraged to share their ideas, push boundaries, take calculated risks, and witness their visions come to life. 

Think you have what it takes? We'd love to meet you!

Job Information
Job Title:¬†Contact Centre Data Analyst¬†
Job Requisition ID:¬†78507
Ministry:¬†Technology and Innovation
Location: Greater Edmonton Area (Remote)¬†
Full or Part-Time:¬†Full Time
Hours of Work:¬†36.25¬†hours per week
Permanent/Temporary: Permanent
Scope:¬†Open Competition
Closing Date: February 26th, 2026
Classification: Systems Analyst 2¬†
Salary: ‚Äã$3,115.21 - $4,277.30/Biweekly ($81,306 - $111,637/ per year)

Technology and Innovation Ministry is responsible for making innovation and technology the driving force behind Alberta‚Äôs economic growth and diversification. To learn more about us, please visit:¬†https://www.alberta.ca/technology-and-innovation

¬†
The Business Technology Operations (BTO) branch creates, maintains, delivers and continually improves IT services consumed by clients. BTO delivers varied IT services related to audit, development, infrastructure, integration, maintenance, operations, platforms, project delivery, quality, service design, service desk, telecommunications and more.

The passionate and solutions focused people that we hire help us to drive vital programs and services that affect Albertans. Whatever your position is here, you will be a part of something great.

Join us !

¬†

Role Responsibilities

Are you passionate about using data and emerging technologies to improve public services? This role puts analytics and innovation at the heart of GoA contact centre operations.

This position is critical to supporting all GoA contact centres and the Albertans they serve by enabling data-driven decision-making and advanced analytics to ensure efficient, responsive service delivery. Reporting to the Manager, Contact Centre Business Support, the Data Analyst gathers, cleans, and maintains large volumes of contact centre data to ensure accuracy and usability for reporting, analytics, and AI-enabled tools.

The role focuses on enhancing the contact centre and reporting platforms, analyzing operational data to identify trends and opportunities for improvement, and defining and monitoring analytics and AI performance metrics. By integrating data from CXone and ServiceNow, the analyst provides a comprehensive view of client journeys and service interactions. The Data Analyst develops and automates dashboards and reports that deliver actionable insights, communicates findings clearly to stakeholders, and works closely with technical teams on platform enhancements, agile projects, and continuous improvement initiatives.

This role is essential to leveraging data, analytics, and AI to drive operational excellence and innovation across GoA contact centres. While prior AI experience is not required, a strong interest or willingness to learn AI is critical. Experience or curiosity in using AI to summarize data, detect anomalies, identify outliers, and automate time-consuming processes will support success in this evolving role.

Responsibilities:
Some of the responsibilities of this position include but are not limited to:

  • Data Analysis & Reporting.
  • Service Operations & Support.
  • Client Service & Collaboration.
  • Continuous Improvement.


To be successful in this position, you will demonstrate:

  • Strong teamwork skills, including the ability to follow direction, mentor and support colleagues, and meet deadlines.
  • Excellent communication skills, with the ability to convey complex information to staff with varying levels of system knowledge.
  • The ability to positively influence, negotiate, and gain commitment from others.
  • Capacity to manage multiple projects under pressure while meeting required time frames.
  • High levels of motivation, creativity, and initiative.
  • Strategic thinking, with the ability to understand outcomes and impacts.
  • Strong analytical, planning, organizational, evaluation, and problem-solving skills.


Future-Focused Skills Matter
While prior AI experience is not required, we're looking for candidates with a strong interest in emerging technologies and a genuine enthusiasm for improving and automating time consuming processes. The ideal candidate should be eager to learn AI to summarize data, identify anomalies, detect outliers etc.


Please click on this link to view the job description for this position.

APS Competencies

Competencies are behaviors that are essential to reach our goals in serving Albertans. We encourage you to have an in depth understanding of the competencies that are required for this opportunity and to be prepared to demonstrate them during the recruitment process.

This link will assist you with understanding competencies:

https://www.alberta.ca/system/files/custom_downloaded_images/psc-alberta-public-service-competency-model.pdf.

¬†

  • Agility: Ability to anticipate, assess, and readily adapt to changing priorities, manage resilience in times of uncertainty and effectively work in a changing environment.
  • Creative Problem Solving: Ability to assess options and implications in new ways to achieve outcomes and solutions.
  • Develop Networks:¬†Leverages relationships to build input and perspective. Looks broadly to engage stakeholders. Open to perspectives towards long-term goals. Actively seeks input into change initiatives. Maintains stakeholder relationships.
  • Systems Thinking:¬†The work done within the APS is part of a larger integrated and inter-related environment. It is important to know that work done in one part of the APS impacts a variety of other groups/projects inside and outside the APS. Systems thinking allows us to keep broader impacts and connections in mind.

Qualifications

Required:

¬†

  • University degree in a related field such as Computer Science, Information Technology.¬†
  • 2 years of related experience working with:
    • Large enterprise data, cloud Solutions such as Contact Centre as a Service (CCaaS).
    • Technical components, data analytics, visualizations.
    • Structured and unstructured data (JSON-style data).
    • Solid understanding of ETL and ELT patterns, incremental loads, late-arriving data, handling time zones/interval buckets, and auditability.
    • Solid experience with Power BI and enterprise reporting tools.
    • Data storytelling, facilitation, translating business queries into metics.

¬†

  • Excellent communication and interpersonal skills.

¬†

Equivalencies: Equivalencies are considered: ¬†

¬†

  • A ¬†related two-year diploma from a recognized post-secondary institution and four (4) years related experience; or
  • A related one-year certificate from a recognized post-secondary institution and five (5) years of related experience.

¬†

Assets:

¬†

  • Experitse in change management and information management methodologies.
  • Broad understanding of the technical environment and linkages between systems
  • Strong technical, and problem-solving skills.
  • Ability to detect and repair problems, independently and quickly.
  • Ability to research issues accurately to identify and solve problems.
  • Experience in preparing professional presentations and training materials and conduct training sessions.
  • Experience in NICE InContact.¬†
  • Experience in ServiceNow.
  • Expertise in languages (SQL) and experience working with relational databases, query authoring (SQL) as well as working familiarity with a variety of databases.

¬†

How To Apply
Applicants are advised to provide information that clearly and concisely demonstrates how their qualifications meet the advertised requirements, including education, experience, and relevant examples of required competencies.

Candidates are required to apply for a job online. Please visit https://www.alberta.ca/job-application-resources#before for more information. Please visit Recruitment Principles, for more information.

In your resume, please include dates (including months and years) associated with all education and work experience. For example, January 2006 - June 2009 (part-time). This example is provided for illustrative purposes only. Applicants are encouraged to present their information clearly and thoroughly, using a format that best conveys their experience.

It is recommended applicants who have completed post-secondary studies from outside of Canada obtain an evaluation of their credentials from the International Qualifications Assessment Service (IQAS)(https://www.alberta.ca/international-qualifications-assessment.aspx) or from a recognized Canadian Credential Evaluator; please visit the Alliance of Credential Evaluation Services of Canada for more information (https://canalliance.org/en/default.html).

It is recommended that applicants include the assessment certificate from IQAS or any other educational assessment service as part of their application.

Closing Statement
This competition may be used to fill future vacancies, across the Government of Alberta, at the same or lower classification level.

We thank all applicants for their interest. All applications will be reviewed to determine which candidates' qualifications most closely match the advertised requirements. Only individuals selected for interviews will be contacted.

If you require any further information on this job posting or require an accommodation during the recruitment process, please contact Michelle Elliott at¬†Michelle.Elliott@gov.ab.ca.¬†
